1
00:00:57,664 --> 00:01:03,081
Oh, great soul!

2
00:01:04,081 --> 00:01:08,331
Oh, great sage!

3
00:01:09,581 --> 00:01:12,123
What is darkness?

4
00:01:12,206 --> 00:01:14,956
SHRI KANAKADURGA CHILI YARD

5
00:01:15,456 --> 00:01:20,331
What is life?
What is death?

6
00:01:20,831 --> 00:01:25,706
What is virtue?
What is sin?

7
00:01:26,039 --> 00:01:30,789
What is hell?
What is heaven?

8
00:01:31,123 --> 00:01:35,873
What is true?
What is not?

9
00:01:36,414 --> 00:01:41,206
What is temporary?
What is permanent?

10
00:01:41,748 --> 00:01:46,331
Which is one?
Which is many?

11
00:01:46,831 --> 00:01:51,706
What is cause?
What is action?

12
00:01:51,998 --> 00:01:55,956
Oh, great soul!

13
00:01:57,206 --> 00:02:00,873
Oh, great sage!

14
00:02:02,623 --> 00:02:07,456
Which is white?
Which is black?

15
00:02:07,998 --> 00:02:12,581
What is song?
What is silence?

16
00:02:13,164 --> 00:02:17,998
Which is mine?
Which is yours?

17
00:02:18,456 --> 00:02:23,039
What is ethics?
What is not?

18
00:02:23,539 --> 00:02:28,456
Yesterday's dream is today's truth

19
00:02:28,831 --> 00:02:33,373
Today's distress is tomorrow's melody

20
00:02:34,081 --> 00:02:38,706
Same brilliance, same peace

21
00:02:39,331 --> 00:02:42,623
Oh, great sage!

22
00:02:45,873 --> 00:02:49,539
Oh, great soul!

23
00:02:58,039 --> 00:02:58,956
Hey!

24
00:03:00,664 --> 00:03:01,581
Rangam, what's that?

25
00:03:01,789 --> 00:03:03,248
It's our warehouse, brother-in-law!

26
00:03:03,539 --> 00:03:04,456
Hey!

27
00:03:04,539 --> 00:03:05,789
Hey, who is that?

28
00:03:05,873 --> 00:03:07,914
- Uncle, take this.
- Hey, go!

29
00:03:07,998 --> 00:03:09,289
Beat those idiots to a pulp!

30
00:03:09,914 --> 00:03:11,081
Hey, move!

31
00:03:23,039 --> 00:03:24,123
Where are you off to?

32
00:03:25,456 --> 00:03:26,373
Hey!

33
00:03:30,581 --> 00:03:31,998
How dare you hit my brother!

34
00:03:34,873 --> 00:03:35,748
Hey!

35
00:03:36,081 --> 00:03:37,706
How dare
you touch my brother-in-law!

36
00:03:37,956 --> 00:03:38,873
You…

37
00:03:43,539 --> 00:03:46,039
Hey, Lenin! Lenin!

38
00:03:46,289 --> 00:03:48,039
Hey… Lenin!

39
00:03:50,164 --> 00:03:51,123
Lenin…

40
00:03:52,039 --> 00:03:54,623
Hey, Lenin.
Nothing will happen to you.

41
00:03:54,706 --> 00:03:55,914
- Brother-in-law…
- Hey.

42
00:03:55,998 --> 00:03:57,873
- What have you done?
- I didn't expect this to happen.

43
00:03:58,164 --> 00:03:59,081
Hey!

44
00:03:59,664 --> 00:04:03,414
I will not spare those bloody rogues
who harmed my brother!

45
00:04:03,956 --> 00:04:06,164
Not a single one will be spared.
I will finish them off!

46
00:04:06,248 --> 00:04:08,414
- Lenin, you will be fine.
- Brother-in-law…

47
00:04:08,498 --> 00:04:09,581
- Hey, Satyam!
- Brother-in-law…

48
00:04:09,789 --> 00:04:12,039
If anything happens to my brother,
you will be done for!

49
00:04:14,331 --> 00:04:15,998
- Brother-in-law…
- Hey, Lenin.

50
00:04:16,331 --> 00:04:17,206
Lenin!

51
00:04:26,081 --> 00:04:26,956
Mom!

52
00:04:33,414 --> 00:04:34,289
Mom!

53
00:04:43,039 --> 00:04:44,623
In Dokka Lenin Babu's murder case,

54
00:04:44,748 --> 00:04:47,331
the accused, Bhogineni Satyanarayana,
alias Royal Satyam,

55
00:04:47,498 --> 00:04:50,039
under IPC Section 302 read with 120B,

56
00:04:50,164 --> 00:04:52,623
has been sentenced
to 12 years of imprisonment.

57
00:05:20,081 --> 00:05:21,831
Oh, you peed!

58
00:05:23,039 --> 00:05:27,039
Elephant! Elephant!

59
00:05:27,248 --> 00:05:31,081
- Elephant!
- Grandpa!

60
00:05:31,164 --> 00:05:34,164
AFTER FEW YEARS

61
00:05:34,373 --> 00:05:36,956
- Kata Madhu's here.
- Just say Kata's here!

62
00:05:38,248 --> 00:05:39,498
Bless me, sir.

63
00:05:42,289 --> 00:05:44,123
I have relied on you
for twenty-five years.

64
00:05:44,206 --> 00:05:47,248
I have become an MLA twice.
I have sold half my assets.

65
00:05:47,998 --> 00:05:51,414
I heard we will be getting
the Law Ministry this time.

66
00:05:51,998 --> 00:05:53,456
With your blessings…

67
00:05:54,164 --> 00:05:55,498
I will get down to the job, sir.

68
00:05:56,498 --> 00:05:58,164
Only someone like him who can
request without inhibition

69
00:05:58,248 --> 00:05:59,664
will emerge in politics.

70
00:05:59,789 --> 00:06:00,706
What do you say, Madhu?

71
00:06:01,623 --> 00:06:02,623
Yes, sir. Thank you.

72
00:06:02,706 --> 00:06:03,664
But…

73
00:06:03,789 --> 00:06:06,123
only someone like me, who can decline
without hesitation, will stay on top.

74
00:06:07,789 --> 00:06:10,456
My daughter gets the ministry this time.
You can relax.

75
00:06:10,623 --> 00:06:11,914
What has she
accomplished so far, sir?

76
00:06:13,206 --> 00:06:16,206
Married twice, gave birth to two,
and let go of one. Is that it?

77
00:06:16,706 --> 00:06:18,123
"Why was her firstborn abandoned?"

78
00:06:18,456 --> 00:06:19,956
"Where is he? What is he up to?"

79
00:06:20,039 --> 00:06:22,081
If I arrange a press meet
and ask such questions…

80
00:06:22,914 --> 00:06:25,664
you will make the headlines
and I will make my way to the cabinet.

81
00:06:25,956 --> 00:06:28,206
Well, you need to stay alive
for that to happen.

82
00:06:31,914 --> 00:06:35,706
I, Vyra Vasundhara,
as the Minister of State for Law,

83
00:06:35,789 --> 00:06:40,664
shall discharge my duties
faithfully and conscientiously.

84
00:06:40,873 --> 00:06:45,456
Without fear, bias, or prejudice,

85
00:06:45,539 --> 00:06:48,789
in accordance with
the Constitution and Law,

86
00:06:48,914 --> 00:06:53,998
I shall do right by all manner of people
and I solemnly swear in the name of God.

87
00:07:20,998 --> 00:07:23,289
- Did you get the papers ready, Pani?
- Yes, sir.

88
00:07:29,373 --> 00:07:32,039
Why bother him now
after twenty-five years, sir?

89
00:07:32,373 --> 00:07:33,664
I like doing this.

90
00:07:33,789 --> 00:07:34,998
Has she asked?

91
00:07:35,081 --> 00:07:37,498
How her former son is and so on?

92
00:07:37,581 --> 00:07:40,498
Actually, I'm overcome with love
for my grandson and I want him here.

93
00:07:40,581 --> 00:07:42,164
You probably think
you can still carry him.

94
00:07:42,373 --> 00:07:43,706
He is more than six feet tall now.

95
00:07:45,039 --> 00:07:45,956
His name is Ramana…

96
00:07:47,164 --> 00:07:49,206
but he's as hot and spicy
as Guntur pepper to touch.

97
00:07:50,748 --> 00:07:52,706
Pepper bales, loading trucks…

98
00:07:53,039 --> 00:07:54,039
It's a world in itself.

99
00:07:54,873 --> 00:07:56,081
And he's the king of that world.

100
00:07:57,831 --> 00:08:02,206
He is already in great form waging wars
and brandishing swords in his kingdom.

101
00:08:02,998 --> 00:08:04,664
We shouldn't invite him
and voluntarily get beaten, sir.

102
00:08:04,789 --> 00:08:07,789
He might be a king there,
but he is no more than a son here.

103
00:08:09,123 --> 00:08:10,539
We will manage. Call him.

104
00:08:13,206 --> 00:08:14,331
Should I call him home, sir?

105
00:08:14,498 --> 00:08:17,331
If we call him home, we will have
to entertain him until he leaves.

106
00:08:17,956 --> 00:08:18,956
Call him to the office.

107
00:08:19,164 --> 00:08:21,081
We can get up and go
once our job is done.

108
00:08:21,164 --> 00:08:22,123
Okay, sir.

109
00:08:23,414 --> 00:08:24,748
- Yeah, okay.
- Hey!

110
00:08:25,164 --> 00:08:26,623
- Grandpa.
- What is the status?

111
00:08:29,331 --> 00:08:31,123
I just had my breakfast.

112
00:08:31,498 --> 00:08:33,206
I also had my coffee.

113
00:08:33,498 --> 00:08:37,498
In a while, Mom will also leave
for the government office.

114
00:08:37,956 --> 00:08:39,164
Correct? Yeah.

115
00:08:39,456 --> 00:08:40,414
Bye!

116
00:08:42,664 --> 00:08:44,248
He makes me wonder…

117
00:08:45,248 --> 00:08:46,623
Is it necessary to call the other guy?

118
00:08:46,706 --> 00:08:49,748
He makes me feel certain
that it is actually an emergency.

119
00:08:54,081 --> 00:08:57,123
SUBURB OF GUNTUR

120
00:09:00,956 --> 00:09:02,873
- Who is it, Dad?
- It's Pani.

121
00:09:03,331 --> 00:09:04,748
He's been continuously calling me
for the past ten days.

122
00:09:05,206 --> 00:09:06,748
"Is Ramana coming to Hyderabad?"

123
00:09:07,956 --> 00:09:09,373
Why don't you go and ask him?

124
00:09:09,498 --> 00:09:11,373
No way!
You know he is short-tempered.

125
00:09:11,539 --> 00:09:13,039
- He will shout at me.
- Why shouldn't he?

126
00:09:13,539 --> 00:09:15,039
He was disowned by his mom
when he was just ten.

127
00:09:15,789 --> 00:09:16,914
Do you expect him to be cheerful?

128
00:09:19,331 --> 00:09:20,539
That's not temper.

129
00:09:21,248 --> 00:09:22,123
That's anguish.

130
00:09:23,164 --> 00:09:24,123
Guntur chili powder.

131
00:09:27,914 --> 00:09:30,998
See… it's red and spicy to look at.

132
00:09:33,873 --> 00:09:35,914
Once it touches your tongue,

133
00:09:36,664 --> 00:09:38,081
there's no way you can stop your tears.

134
00:09:41,039 --> 00:09:42,081
He is no different.

135
00:09:43,039 --> 00:09:45,456
He seems harsh
but is actually sweet.

136
00:09:45,664 --> 00:09:47,331
Ask him yourself.
You'll know how sweet he is.

137
00:09:47,414 --> 00:09:48,498
What do we ask him?

138
00:09:48,956 --> 00:09:50,164
His mom is calling him.

139
00:09:50,498 --> 00:09:52,539
Asking him to meet her is wrong.
Telling him not to is also wrong.

140
00:09:53,123 --> 00:09:54,289
I dice with death!

141
00:09:54,539 --> 00:09:55,748
What are you looking at?

142
00:09:56,456 --> 00:09:58,123
We got to move three full loads of chili.

143
00:09:58,498 --> 00:10:00,373
Bandar Route seems to be good.
Take the same route.

144
00:10:01,206 --> 00:10:03,248
- Call me as soon as you reach.
- Yes.

145
00:10:03,331 --> 00:10:05,289
"We didn't want to disturb you at night."

146
00:10:05,498 --> 00:10:09,581
If you come up with such lame excuses,
I will flay your skin, morons!

147
00:10:10,123 --> 00:10:11,498
Go! Get going!

148
00:10:19,123 --> 00:10:19,998
What?

149
00:10:20,289 --> 00:10:21,164
Well…

150
00:10:21,498 --> 00:10:23,706
Pani has been asking
if you have started for Hyderabad yet.

151
00:10:24,748 --> 00:10:25,748
Should I go?

152
00:10:25,873 --> 00:10:28,039
I'm not able to say yes
because I know they are not fair people.

153
00:10:28,748 --> 00:10:30,623
Of course, there is nothing
to say about you.

154
00:10:32,248 --> 00:10:33,456
Is that a yes or a no?

155
00:10:33,581 --> 00:10:35,539
If I knew that,
why would I stretch so much?

156
00:10:45,539 --> 00:10:46,873
- Hey, Samba.
- Yeah?

157
00:10:48,498 --> 00:10:50,039
Do you think she will recognize me?

158
00:10:50,331 --> 00:10:51,206
Yes.

159
00:11:05,206 --> 00:11:07,331
- Is there enough diesel in the car?
- Tank's full, cousin.

160
00:11:07,539 --> 00:11:08,414
What is the address?

161
00:11:08,498 --> 00:11:10,664
Abids, Janadalam Party Office, Hyderabad.

162
00:11:10,748 --> 00:11:11,914
I was told that
anyone would guide you there.

163
00:11:17,248 --> 00:11:18,373
- Are the papers ready?
- Yes, sir.

164
00:11:19,789 --> 00:11:21,039
I hope there are no spelling mistakes.

165
00:11:21,289 --> 00:11:23,164
She divorced her husband
and abandoned her son.

166
00:11:23,248 --> 00:11:24,748
She remarried and had another son.

167
00:11:24,873 --> 00:11:27,331
The first son has no right to her assets.
This is all we've written.

168
00:11:27,414 --> 00:11:29,664
This statement is a mistake in itself and
you're asking me for spelling mistakes?

169
00:11:30,373 --> 00:11:31,248
His name is Ramana.

170
00:11:31,706 --> 00:11:32,706
Hold this and stand.

171
00:11:33,539 --> 00:11:35,706
- Has nobody seen him in all these years?
- There was no time.

172
00:11:35,914 --> 00:11:37,456
This is not a mistake, sir.
It's a blunder.

173
00:11:37,831 --> 00:11:40,164
Not that. This is a blunder.

174
00:11:40,248 --> 00:11:41,123
Give it!

175
00:11:49,289 --> 00:11:51,498
RAMANA

176
00:11:55,081 --> 00:11:56,998
Spicy and pungent!

177
00:11:58,623 --> 00:12:00,789
Stinging chili powder!

178
00:12:12,914 --> 00:12:16,956
Iron bar, heavy hammer
A single blow and broken by sparks!

179
00:12:34,914 --> 00:12:36,748
My left eye is a bit weak, man!

180
00:12:37,498 --> 00:12:38,373
Come here.

181
00:12:41,206 --> 00:12:42,414
You are…

182
00:12:42,748 --> 00:12:44,081
Are you thrilled to see me?

183
00:12:45,331 --> 00:12:46,414
Did your heart rate go up?

184
00:12:47,914 --> 00:12:48,998
Did you feel like whistling?

185
00:12:50,789 --> 00:12:51,664
It's Ramana.

186
00:12:51,831 --> 00:12:52,956
Nice to meet you, sir!

187
00:12:56,914 --> 00:12:57,956
What's the buzz here?

188
00:12:59,081 --> 00:13:01,039
The old man is turning eighty, sir.

189
00:13:01,248 --> 00:13:02,206
You know…

190
00:13:02,914 --> 00:13:04,873
Most useless things last long.

191
00:13:06,373 --> 00:13:08,081
So much hubbub for his birthday!

192
00:13:09,289 --> 00:13:10,623
What will you do when he dies?

193
00:13:11,956 --> 00:13:13,289
Break open the earth?

194
00:13:13,581 --> 00:13:14,873
That was deep, sir.

195
00:13:16,373 --> 00:13:17,373
Where is Pani?

196
00:13:18,414 --> 00:13:19,373
He is waiting in there, sir.

197
00:13:19,456 --> 00:13:20,623
- This is his obligation.
- Yes, sir.

198
00:13:20,706 --> 00:13:22,164
What else can he do besides wait?

199
00:13:39,081 --> 00:13:39,956
Mom!

200
00:13:43,081 --> 00:13:44,039
Mom!

201
00:13:50,581 --> 00:13:51,581
That way…

202
00:13:51,998 --> 00:13:52,914
Sir?

203
00:13:58,039 --> 00:13:59,289
Why is he blocking my way?

204
00:13:59,873 --> 00:14:00,831
That way, sir.

205
00:14:01,164 --> 00:14:02,873
Doesn't he know what she is to me?

206
00:14:03,039 --> 00:14:03,956
Mother?

207
00:14:04,206 --> 00:14:06,331
She was called "sister" when she was
younger. Now, they call her "mother".

208
00:14:06,581 --> 00:14:07,706
Go get an appointment first.

209
00:14:10,081 --> 00:14:12,498
Along with safari, he also sports satire.

210
00:14:17,914 --> 00:14:19,456
What are you looking at?
Will you hit me?

211
00:14:21,373 --> 00:14:23,498
Just wondering if I should kill you!

212
00:14:24,456 --> 00:14:25,956
Whoa!

213
00:14:26,164 --> 00:14:28,539
Son! Son, this way.

214
00:14:28,914 --> 00:14:29,873
This way.

215
00:14:32,956 --> 00:14:33,914
Coffee? Tea?

216
00:14:34,664 --> 00:14:35,748
Is there a cup in your hand?

217
00:14:37,081 --> 00:14:38,123
Only papers, right?

218
00:14:39,081 --> 00:14:40,206
Give me a pen.
I'll sign and leave.

219
00:14:42,498 --> 00:14:44,123
You better read it before signing, sir.

220
00:14:45,123 --> 00:14:46,498
I should be killing you.

221
00:14:47,623 --> 00:14:50,039
What could be so disruptive?

222
00:14:50,539 --> 00:14:53,248
"Don't claim a legacy."
You don't need it.

223
00:14:53,789 --> 00:14:56,664
"Don't use the surname."
You have your paternal surname anyway.

224
00:14:57,039 --> 00:14:59,081
In short, you have no relation
with this family.

225
00:14:59,914 --> 00:15:01,373
As if it has existed all these years!

226
00:15:01,581 --> 00:15:03,956
In agreement, a signature…

227
00:15:04,039 --> 00:15:05,623
When you part ways from
your husband, it's called a divorce.

228
00:15:06,539 --> 00:15:07,831
When you disown your son,
what's the term for it?

229
00:15:09,789 --> 00:15:11,123
Did you think of a name?

230
00:15:12,164 --> 00:15:13,456
If yes, ask her to come and tell me.

231
00:15:13,914 --> 00:15:16,373
Why just one?
I'll put a hundred signatures.

232
00:15:18,914 --> 00:15:20,456
How is she still his mother?

233
00:15:21,831 --> 00:15:24,456
If he wants, let him see her
when she is on TV.

234
00:15:26,289 --> 00:15:28,289
He doesn't have a mother,
and he won't be getting one now.

235
00:15:28,581 --> 00:15:29,498
Go, tell him.

236
00:15:29,748 --> 00:15:32,664
- What if he doesn't agree?
- Destruction…

237
00:15:33,998 --> 00:15:35,414
I will destroy him.

238
00:15:37,539 --> 00:15:40,164
Ensure that emphasis
is placed on "destruction."

239
00:15:40,706 --> 00:15:43,539
If we place emphasis on it,
he'll probably not sign the paper, sir.

240
00:15:44,789 --> 00:15:47,956
No, I mean, why call him here
yourself and then provoke him?

241
00:15:48,039 --> 00:15:51,539
If he realizes we are in need,
he may raise his price, Pani.

242
00:15:52,206 --> 00:15:54,623
We must keep him at a distance
and get the work done.

243
00:15:58,289 --> 00:16:01,581
When we ask for votes,
we even enter huts.

244
00:16:02,456 --> 00:16:06,039
Once we win, do we allow the voters
to come into our homes?

245
00:16:07,373 --> 00:16:08,664
It's the same with him.

246
00:16:10,373 --> 00:16:14,081
While he is still under the illusion
of seeing or meeting his mother,

247
00:16:14,164 --> 00:16:16,206
we should get the job done.

248
00:16:17,039 --> 00:16:17,914
Go, tell him.

249
00:16:17,998 --> 00:16:19,331
Which one? About the voters, sir?

250
00:16:19,456 --> 00:16:21,498
- What I told you before that.
- Okay, sir.

251
00:16:54,706 --> 00:16:56,789
I got it signed, sir.

252
00:16:58,748 --> 00:17:00,623
Why do you take the trouble, sir?
Let me check this for you.

253
00:17:01,331 --> 00:17:02,623
- Oh…
- Give it here.

254
00:17:03,706 --> 00:17:04,581
Sir!

255
00:17:07,581 --> 00:17:09,998
LOOKING FORWARD TO THE DESTRUCTION
YOU WILL CREATE

256
00:17:22,581 --> 00:17:23,831
It's just a signature.
Why are you laughing?

257
00:17:23,914 --> 00:17:25,539
- The old man will kill you. Stop it!
- Hey!

258
00:17:27,373 --> 00:17:28,414
Give it here.

259
00:17:28,789 --> 00:17:29,706
Hey!

260
00:17:30,081 --> 00:17:31,373
- What happened? Tell me.
- Sorry, sir.

261
00:17:31,498 --> 00:17:34,289
Looking forward to the destruction
you will create.

262
00:17:34,373 --> 00:17:39,206
He has emphasized "destruction", sir.

263
00:18:33,998 --> 00:18:35,123
JANADALAM PARTY

264
00:19:17,248 --> 00:19:18,289
His name is Ramana…

265
00:19:18,789 --> 00:19:21,539
but he's as hot and spicy
as Guntur pepper to touch.

266
00:19:39,164 --> 00:19:43,873
It stings! This boy's chili powder!
Business with him is a roller coaster

267
00:19:44,123 --> 00:19:50,706
Hot and spicy is his chili powder
Business with him is a roller coaster

268
00:19:50,789 --> 00:19:53,456
Hey, on the road to Pattabhipuram
You may ask anyone

269
00:19:53,539 --> 00:19:56,164
There's no one who doesn't know
This boy from Burripalem

270
00:19:56,289 --> 00:19:57,998
Hey, there's no one who doesn't know him

271
00:19:58,081 --> 00:20:00,748
Hey, he looks all glorious
But is good at battering, mother promise!

272
00:20:00,831 --> 00:20:03,123
When he strikes, brain freezes
And they forget the pin code

273
00:20:03,206 --> 00:20:04,164
Fair!

274
00:20:05,289 --> 00:20:06,414
Hey, crazy!

275
00:20:07,789 --> 00:20:08,831
Stinging!

276
00:20:08,956 --> 00:20:12,873
Hey, he's like a stinging slap!

277
00:20:12,956 --> 00:20:15,248
Fair in complexion
With mind-blowing speed

278
00:20:15,331 --> 00:20:17,706
A stinging burn
He is highly inflammable

279
00:20:17,789 --> 00:20:20,456
Everybody, make way
Leader on the way

280
00:20:20,539 --> 00:20:22,623
Ain't got no time to play

281
00:20:27,706 --> 00:20:32,331
Though the wind moving against me
Blows away the top button

282
00:20:32,498 --> 00:20:37,164
It plunges straight ahead
The vehicle I board

283
00:20:37,456 --> 00:20:39,789
No one to account for

284
00:20:39,873 --> 00:20:42,289
No one to endorse for

285
00:20:42,373 --> 00:20:46,789
A burden loaded by others
Why should I carry it on my shoulders?

286
00:20:46,873 --> 00:20:51,706
Slow-cooked spicy biryani
Red chili half tandoori

287
00:20:51,789 --> 00:20:56,539
With lemon soda and a cigarette
Make your stamp on Guntur

288
00:20:56,623 --> 00:21:01,373
Slow-cooked spicy biryani
Red chili half tandoori

289
00:21:01,456 --> 00:21:06,373
With lemon soda and a cigarette
Make your stamp on Guntur

290
00:21:06,456 --> 00:21:11,331
I am silence infinite
Waging a war with myself

291
00:21:11,414 --> 00:21:16,081
A bit of selfishness and a bit of virtue
I am love-matter with a mix of these

292
00:21:35,164 --> 00:21:37,706
Hey, hold it, beauty
Hold the pestle high

293
00:21:37,789 --> 00:21:41,831
Bring it down one after one
And pound it to your maximum

294
00:21:41,998 --> 00:21:43,789
Pound it!

295
00:21:44,831 --> 00:21:47,414
Hey, one chili per pound
Sacrifice it to the stone

296
00:21:47,498 --> 00:21:51,539
Making the chili spicier
Filling the air with aroma

297
00:21:54,539 --> 00:21:56,164
Tuck in your sari

298
00:21:56,873 --> 00:21:58,623
And change hands slowly

299
00:21:59,289 --> 00:22:01,664
Hey, add some strength
And make the seed flat

300
00:22:01,748 --> 00:22:04,414
Empty the vessel of fresh chili powder

301
00:22:14,123 --> 00:22:18,914
My heart is my window
And I close it at my will

302
00:22:18,998 --> 00:22:23,081
The wounds of tomorrow
I avert them right now

303
00:22:23,164 --> 00:22:26,456
My destiny is a colorful pattern

304
00:22:26,539 --> 00:22:28,831
I may be sad
But won't stop the celebration

305
00:22:28,914 --> 00:22:33,539
My own fort of laughter
Why should I destroy it?

306
00:22:33,623 --> 00:22:38,289
Slow cooked spicy biryani
Red chili half tandoori

307
00:22:38,373 --> 00:22:43,123
With lemon soda and a cigarette
Make your stamp on Guntur

308
00:22:43,206 --> 00:22:47,998
Slow cooked spicy biryani
Red chili half tandoori

309
00:22:48,081 --> 00:22:53,164
With lemon soda and a cigarette
Make your stamp on Guntur

310
00:23:13,706 --> 00:23:14,664
Mom!

311
00:23:14,873 --> 00:23:15,956
Ramana is here!

312
00:23:16,248 --> 00:23:17,123
What?

313
00:23:17,206 --> 00:23:18,164
Ramana is here!

314
00:23:18,248 --> 00:23:20,414
What are you saying?
I can't hear you! Come again!

315
00:23:22,498 --> 00:23:24,123
Mom, Ramana is here.

316
00:23:24,206 --> 00:23:26,289
If you could shout it from upstairs,
why bother rushing down?

317
00:23:27,164 --> 00:23:28,748
Your wife cannot hear.

318
00:23:29,039 --> 00:23:30,623
He's already at the door.
He would come in anyway.

319
00:23:31,039 --> 00:23:32,623
If the door is shut,
he will go wherever he wants.

320
00:23:32,789 --> 00:23:34,581
Hey, Ramana.
How did it go?

321
00:23:34,664 --> 00:23:36,414
- Count or deal?
- Drop.

322
00:23:36,748 --> 00:23:39,414
Hey, you never get a life in cards.
Nor wisdom in life.

323
00:23:39,581 --> 00:23:41,331
Does context mean anything to you?

324
00:23:42,914 --> 00:23:44,123
How is your mother?

325
00:23:44,206 --> 00:23:45,289
Has she put on weight?

326
00:23:45,873 --> 00:23:47,414
She is glowing
like a Goddess in a temple.

327
00:23:47,498 --> 00:23:48,748
You should have performed arti then!

328
00:23:49,164 --> 00:23:50,206
I didn't find the matches.

329
00:23:50,289 --> 00:23:52,414
But you find packs of them
for lighting cigarettes.

330
00:23:52,498 --> 00:23:53,498
Yeah, right.

331
00:23:53,748 --> 00:23:55,706
I'm famished.
What did you cook?

332
00:23:55,998 --> 00:23:57,164
Nothing special.

333
00:23:57,414 --> 00:23:58,998
I have only made egg curry.

334
00:23:59,956 --> 00:24:00,914
Aunty!

335
00:24:01,498 --> 00:24:03,248
Bring the egg here.
I will eat it.

336
00:24:05,498 --> 00:24:07,914
- What?
- One of your eyes doesn't work anyway.

337
00:24:08,289 --> 00:24:09,914
Do these sunglasses
make it any better?

338
00:24:09,998 --> 00:24:10,914
Damn!

339
00:24:11,331 --> 00:24:12,956
You cannot handle my style.

340
00:24:15,539 --> 00:24:16,748
Did she ask you
how you have been?

341
00:24:16,831 --> 00:24:18,164
She broke down as soon as she saw me.

342
00:24:18,331 --> 00:24:19,289
Really?

343
00:24:20,539 --> 00:24:22,123
She said, "Why should you eat
your aunt's awful egg curry?

344
00:24:22,248 --> 00:24:23,831
Stay back. I will make chicken for you."

345
00:24:24,414 --> 00:24:25,706
- Well, you should have!
- Oh!

346
00:24:25,789 --> 00:24:27,289
I didn't want you to miss me.
So, here I am.

347
00:24:27,956 --> 00:24:30,456
Hey, what is that half-hearted serving?
He's growing up. Eat this.

348
00:24:30,539 --> 00:24:32,664
Hey! You want to kill me with eggs?

349
00:24:32,873 --> 00:24:34,789
Yeah, I cannot let go like your mother.

350
00:24:34,914 --> 00:24:36,831
Hey! Allow him to tell us
what happened there.

351
00:24:36,914 --> 00:24:38,539
You haven't given him a break
since he came back!

352
00:24:39,456 --> 00:24:41,456
My brother-in-law only speaks once a year.

353
00:24:41,581 --> 00:24:42,831
But when he does, he is on the dot.

354
00:24:42,914 --> 00:24:44,581
It's not like they were
overcome with love.

355
00:24:46,456 --> 00:24:48,039
They required my signature indicating
I'm nobody to them.

356
00:24:48,581 --> 00:24:49,623
That's why they called me.

357
00:24:52,081 --> 00:24:54,039
- Hey, Samba.
- Yeah?

358
00:24:54,289 --> 00:24:55,623
They say we shouldn't claim their assets.

359
00:24:56,248 --> 00:24:57,289
Have we ever?

360
00:24:58,414 --> 00:24:59,706
She won't see her son…

361
00:25:00,248 --> 00:25:01,873
but sits in the office
behind closed doors.

362
00:25:02,664 --> 00:25:05,123
Since she was so busy, I thought
I shouldn't bother. So, I didn't sign.

363
00:25:08,164 --> 00:25:09,248
Hello, Mr. Satyam!

364
00:25:09,456 --> 00:25:11,373
Go and play the right song
on your gramophone on this occasion.

365
00:25:12,789 --> 00:25:15,748
It should suit the estranged husband
as well as the disowned son.

366
00:25:28,123 --> 00:25:30,956
I can't tell who is laying eggs at home!
You or the chicken!

367
00:25:41,123 --> 00:25:42,498
Didn't you like the dosa, sir?

368
00:25:43,998 --> 00:25:45,789
- I don't feel good, Pani.
- Oh!

369
00:25:45,873 --> 00:25:48,164
You never know when Kata Madhu
would create a nuisance.

370
00:25:48,956 --> 00:25:49,873
True, sir.

371
00:25:50,581 --> 00:25:52,373
Why isn't he signing?

372
00:25:52,873 --> 00:25:53,914
After all, it's his mother.

373
00:25:54,373 --> 00:25:57,123
In that case, call him saying
his mother wants to see him.

374
00:25:59,581 --> 00:26:04,998
Desire puts on wings
Flutters and flies

375
00:26:07,123 --> 00:26:10,456
Losing way, on the starry path
Takes off the celebration

376
00:26:10,581 --> 00:26:11,456
Hey!

377
00:26:11,748 --> 00:26:12,789
Do I ever drink soda?

378
00:26:13,998 --> 00:26:14,956
Sorry about that.

379
00:26:15,373 --> 00:26:17,289
You use water, right?
I'll get it.

380
00:26:17,748 --> 00:26:18,748
Uncle!

381
00:26:18,998 --> 00:26:21,081
Uncle! That's water.
Here, take this.

382
00:26:28,248 --> 00:26:29,164
One minute.

383
00:26:31,789 --> 00:26:33,706
Hey, I prefer an omelet!

384
00:26:34,914 --> 00:26:36,289
Where is your mind at?

385
00:26:43,623 --> 00:26:44,664
What is the problem?

386
00:26:45,539 --> 00:26:47,289
There was a call from
Hyderabad yesterday.

387
00:26:47,873 --> 00:26:49,456
He was asked to come home this time.

388
00:26:50,498 --> 00:26:53,456
Your son is drinking like a fish, Uncle.

389
00:26:54,164 --> 00:26:56,164
By the time I took him some water,
he had finished a quarter.

390
00:26:56,414 --> 00:26:58,914
If I take too long with the omelet,
he might even devour me!

391
00:26:59,831 --> 00:27:01,164
- Don't tell him I told you this.
- Wait.

392
00:27:01,248 --> 00:27:03,331
- Please, don't. He will kill me, Uncle.
- Just wait.

393
00:27:04,081 --> 00:27:05,039
- Hey!
- Uncle…

394
00:27:06,289 --> 00:27:07,248
Ramana!

395
00:27:09,998 --> 00:27:11,039
Are you drinking?

396
00:27:12,748 --> 00:27:14,831
- Did you get a call from Hyderabad?
- Yeah.

397
00:27:15,664 --> 00:27:16,623
What was it about?

398
00:27:16,956 --> 00:27:18,373
They were pleased to see the grandson.

399
00:27:18,581 --> 00:27:19,873
Now, they want to see the son.

400
00:27:20,373 --> 00:27:21,414
You should go then.

401
00:27:21,789 --> 00:27:23,873
For what?
They are closing doors on me.

402
00:27:24,789 --> 00:27:27,789
Break down the doors.
You possess every right as a son.

403
00:27:27,956 --> 00:27:28,914
Is that so?

404
00:27:29,414 --> 00:27:31,456
You sit and gaze out of the window.

405
00:27:31,623 --> 00:27:33,289
But expect me to go there
knocking down doors!

406
00:27:34,373 --> 00:27:37,831
They say when you refuse a meal,
you stay hungry the whole day.

407
00:27:38,456 --> 00:27:42,123
But if you reject your mother,
you will cry all your life.

408
00:27:42,456 --> 00:27:44,789
She has left him,
but he doesn't let go of her.

409
00:27:46,206 --> 00:27:48,081
He thinks she will scoop me up
as soon as I go.

410
00:27:48,456 --> 00:27:49,498
What did you say?

411
00:27:50,539 --> 00:27:51,998
Are you going there or not?

412
00:27:53,039 --> 00:27:54,581
BASAVARAJU SARANGAPANI
B.A, B.L

413
00:27:54,664 --> 00:27:55,998
ADVOCATE

414
00:27:59,706 --> 00:28:01,039
I'm the boss here.

415
00:28:01,289 --> 00:28:03,789
The moment I enter,
they wet their pants out of fear.

416
00:28:04,373 --> 00:28:05,539
Sir! Welcome, sir.

417
00:28:06,039 --> 00:28:07,581
- You are?
- I'm Mr. Pani's assistant, sir.

418
00:28:07,706 --> 00:28:08,789
Don't you have a name?

419
00:28:08,873 --> 00:28:09,956
I'm Balu, sir.

420
00:28:10,123 --> 00:28:12,164
- This is?
- Mr. Pani's house, sir.

421
00:28:12,539 --> 00:28:14,039
Hey, capture well.

422
00:28:14,164 --> 00:28:15,873
I should have everyone floored.

423
00:28:15,998 --> 00:28:16,998
And that is?

424
00:28:17,373 --> 00:28:18,414
Mr. Pani's daughter, sir.

425
00:28:18,831 --> 00:28:21,039
Today's special is my home tour.

426
00:28:21,123 --> 00:28:22,539
This is our tree.

427
00:28:22,623 --> 00:28:24,039
Sister! That's a plant.

428
00:28:24,289 --> 00:28:26,581
When I don't know it myself,
how would the others know? Keep quiet!

429
00:28:27,581 --> 00:28:29,498
Tomorrow is my father's death anniversary.

430
00:28:29,581 --> 00:28:31,164
It's Grandpa's!

431
00:28:31,289 --> 00:28:32,789
Wasn't something of Dad's coming up too?

432
00:28:32,873 --> 00:28:34,164
His birthday.

433
00:28:34,831 --> 00:28:35,956
Both are special occasions.

434
00:28:39,123 --> 00:28:40,248
Jeez!

435
00:28:41,039 --> 00:28:42,581
Pani's daughter is quite ravishing.

436
00:28:43,623 --> 00:28:44,623
Ravishing?

437
00:28:47,414 --> 00:28:48,581
He has come to meet your dad.

438
00:28:48,748 --> 00:28:49,706
He is not home.

439
00:28:49,998 --> 00:28:50,998
We will wait.

440
00:28:52,039 --> 00:28:53,456
Sure. Wait outside.

441
00:28:53,748 --> 00:28:54,664
Hey, girl!

442
00:28:56,248 --> 00:28:57,456
Look at my complexion.

443
00:28:58,998 --> 00:29:00,581
Won't I get tanned sitting in the sun?

444
00:29:00,956 --> 00:29:02,789
Oh, really?
Just a minute.

445
00:29:05,581 --> 00:29:06,706
As if he is a rose!

446
00:29:06,998 --> 00:29:08,081
Wear it in your hair.

447
00:29:10,373 --> 00:29:12,956
So, is that how you speak to all girls?

448
00:29:14,289 --> 00:29:15,956
Not unless they are extremely pretty.

449
00:29:17,623 --> 00:29:18,623
What's your deal?

450
00:29:18,956 --> 00:29:19,873
Not with you.

451
00:29:20,414 --> 00:29:21,331
With your pop.

452
00:29:21,581 --> 00:29:23,998
Pop? What do you mean by "pop"?
Can't you give him some respect?

453
00:29:24,956 --> 00:29:26,248
I guess she is angry.

454
00:29:27,789 --> 00:29:29,873
I offered it.
But he refused.

455
00:29:31,539 --> 00:29:32,498
My goodness!

456
00:29:32,581 --> 00:29:34,831
- Who the heck is he?
- Green really suits her.

457
00:29:35,373 --> 00:29:38,331
Who is this guy flirting so openly?

458
00:29:38,831 --> 00:29:40,873
I spared him because
he's good-looking. Otherwise…

459
00:29:58,873 --> 00:30:00,998
- What's the name though?
- Bala Subramanyam, sir.

460
00:30:01,081 --> 00:30:02,289
Who wants yours?

461
00:30:02,664 --> 00:30:05,039
Amukta Malyada, sir.
We call her Amuda out of love.

462
00:30:05,206 --> 00:30:07,748
Why should you show any love?
Leave that to me.

463
00:30:08,206 --> 00:30:09,456
Won't you give me at least that freedom?

464
00:30:09,623 --> 00:30:10,498
Take it, sir.

465
00:30:12,039 --> 00:30:14,748
Why is she in a sari?
What is the occasion?

466
00:30:14,831 --> 00:30:16,373
She makes Insta reels.

467
00:30:16,456 --> 00:30:18,289
She was in jeans yesterday.
Today she is in a sari.

468
00:30:18,414 --> 00:30:19,831
Could she be wearing a skirt tomorrow?

469
00:30:19,914 --> 00:30:21,581
- Why do you ask, sir?
- I'll come again tomorrow.

470
00:30:21,748 --> 00:30:22,873
Tomorrow is my weekly off, sir.

471
00:30:23,873 --> 00:30:26,248
Mom! That's him.

472
00:30:31,581 --> 00:30:33,498
Are there burglars in their house, Balu?

473
00:30:33,956 --> 00:30:35,414
They are not allowing anybody in!

474
00:30:35,831 --> 00:30:37,248
They won't even offer tea.

475
00:30:37,539 --> 00:30:39,789
That's not the case, sir. This is
the first time they have seen a rowdy.

476
00:30:40,664 --> 00:30:41,539
Sorry, sir.

477
00:30:49,123 --> 00:30:50,289
What did I say earlier?

478
00:30:50,456 --> 00:30:51,998
You said Mr. Pani's daughter is ravishing.

479
00:30:52,081 --> 00:30:53,123
She's not just ravishing.

480
00:30:53,831 --> 00:30:56,081
- She's delightfully ravishing.
- Son!

481
00:30:56,164 --> 00:30:57,873
- Sir!
- Pani, we were just talking about you.

482
00:30:57,956 --> 00:30:59,998
Why did you make him sit here?
Have you any sense?

483
00:31:00,748 --> 00:31:02,039
Please come, sir.
Let's go in and have some coffee.

484
00:31:02,123 --> 00:31:03,123
- Pani…
- Yes?

485
00:31:03,831 --> 00:31:04,873
Was it Mom who called me?

486
00:31:05,581 --> 00:31:06,581
Yes, I swear.

487
00:31:06,789 --> 00:31:07,956
We will have coffee there.
Let's go.

488
00:31:08,039 --> 00:31:09,998
One minute. I will reverse the car.
You please come over.

489
00:31:12,331 --> 00:31:13,289
Ammu!

490
00:31:15,873 --> 00:31:16,831
The name is Ramana.

491
00:31:17,414 --> 00:31:18,414
Remember it.

492
00:31:19,289 --> 00:31:20,623
It will be of use
when you come to Guntur.

493
00:31:22,248 --> 00:31:23,414
He has given you a nickname already.

494
00:31:48,873 --> 00:31:49,956
Hey, it's done. Lift it.

495
00:32:19,373 --> 00:32:21,289
Did he say
I was going to cause destruction?

496
00:32:22,081 --> 00:32:23,789
Did he say I was waiting?

497
00:32:23,914 --> 00:32:24,956
What did you write?

498
00:32:25,789 --> 00:32:26,706
What did you say?

499
00:32:27,956 --> 00:32:29,873
You know I would lie.

500
00:32:31,206 --> 00:32:32,956
You know I am covering up.

501
00:32:35,498 --> 00:32:36,456
Hey!

502
00:32:39,748 --> 00:32:40,873
He is your uncle.

503
00:32:41,414 --> 00:32:43,289
- My daughter's--
- Second husband?

504
00:32:47,456 --> 00:32:49,081
Boss, if you don't mind,
can I ask you something?

505
00:32:49,664 --> 00:32:50,581
Please.

506
00:32:50,831 --> 00:32:52,414
What did my mother see in you
that she married you?

507
00:32:54,456 --> 00:32:57,498
I condemn. Condemn.

508
00:32:57,664 --> 00:33:00,748
Grandpa! In what context
can we use "condemn"?

509
00:33:00,831 --> 00:33:03,331
Your father can condemn him
for his question.

510
00:33:04,789 --> 00:33:05,664
Who is this guy?

511
00:33:05,748 --> 00:33:08,998
To this family and our constituency,
he is the only heir.

512
00:33:09,248 --> 00:33:10,914
- Who is this gentleman?
- Your brother by relation.

513
00:33:11,081 --> 00:33:11,956
You can go.

514
00:33:12,456 --> 00:33:13,414
Hey!

515
00:33:13,789 --> 00:33:15,289
Don't walk away in such a peculiar manner!

516
00:33:15,706 --> 00:33:18,123
Weren't you taught
how to greet your elders?

517
00:33:24,081 --> 00:33:25,539
- Namaste!
- I see!

518
00:33:30,956 --> 00:33:32,998
You and your stupid Hindi greetings!

519
00:33:33,373 --> 00:33:34,581
I condemn this!

520
00:33:34,956 --> 00:33:37,206
I bless you. Now get going.

521
00:33:39,206 --> 00:33:41,039
All the characters are here.

522
00:33:42,456 --> 00:33:44,206
But where is the main lead?

523
00:33:45,164 --> 00:33:46,873
Have you locked her up inside?

524
00:33:47,831 --> 00:33:50,164
Sign this first.
She will come.

525
00:33:50,331 --> 00:33:53,248
Let her come first.
I will sign.

526
00:33:53,456 --> 00:33:56,414
The other day when he was at the office,
if only we had given him a good beating…

527
00:33:56,498 --> 00:33:58,081
Beating, my foot!

528
00:33:58,164 --> 00:33:59,248
Hey!

529
00:33:59,331 --> 00:34:01,456
You don't have to shout.
I can hear properly.

530
00:34:02,039 --> 00:34:03,623
You are old and hard of hearing.

531
00:34:04,206 --> 00:34:06,456
- I should be shouting.
- Who are you calling old?

532
00:34:06,873 --> 00:34:07,789
Who…

533
00:34:08,123 --> 00:34:09,581
- Father-in-law!
- Sir!

534
00:34:09,664 --> 00:34:11,164
Who is an old man?

535
00:34:12,206 --> 00:34:13,289
Who is old here?

536
00:34:13,373 --> 00:34:15,956
Are you going to get up and dance
to prove that you are not old?

537
00:34:22,081 --> 00:34:23,081
On this one?

538
00:34:24,164 --> 00:34:25,206
You want my signature?

539
00:34:30,914 --> 00:34:33,706
I only sign autographs for my fans,
not just anyone and everyone.

540
00:34:33,956 --> 00:34:35,164
Superb!

541
00:34:37,498 --> 00:34:39,789
I guess he doesn't need any medicine.
He has stopped coughing all of a sudden.

542
00:35:05,956 --> 00:35:07,706
Why bother the old guy, sir?
Why don't you just sign it?

543
00:35:09,914 --> 00:35:11,498
There is a love story going on here.

544
00:35:12,873 --> 00:35:14,831
I should know whether
it's a one-sided or two-way situation.

545
00:35:16,164 --> 00:35:17,248
I won't sign until then.

546
00:35:55,289 --> 00:35:57,206
Why do you keep provoking him, sir?

547
00:35:59,039 --> 00:36:01,331
In my opinion, it was wrong
to talk to him in the first place.

548
00:36:01,831 --> 00:36:02,873
Fine, you did.

549
00:36:04,081 --> 00:36:05,748
She has disowned him for 25 years.

550
00:36:06,581 --> 00:36:07,956
You should have done the same.

551
00:36:08,039 --> 00:36:09,581
That won't do.

552
00:36:11,123 --> 00:36:13,748
He should stop believing
that my daughter is his mother.

553
00:36:14,039 --> 00:36:16,206
Or we should make him stop?
That is why…

554
00:36:16,873 --> 00:36:19,664
it's imperative he signs the document
saying he is in no way related to us.

555
00:36:20,081 --> 00:36:22,539
That way, my grandson will have
no hurdles. He will become an MP.

556
00:36:22,998 --> 00:36:24,581
Ramana will confine himself to Guntur.

557
00:36:24,706 --> 00:36:26,039
Madhu will be out of power.

558
00:36:27,248 --> 00:36:28,831
The requirement is yours,
and the signature is his.

559
00:36:28,914 --> 00:36:30,623
How am I concerned?

560
00:36:30,706 --> 00:36:32,123
Because, Pani…

561
00:36:32,289 --> 00:36:35,373
Venkata Swamy never takes
no for an answer.

562
00:36:36,623 --> 00:36:38,956
There is no one who wished to make him.
They are dead.

563
00:36:44,581 --> 00:36:48,664
SHRI KANAKADURGA CHILI YARD

564
00:36:49,539 --> 00:36:50,498
Hi, sir.

565
00:36:52,248 --> 00:36:53,914
- Hey, Balu.
- Sir!

566
00:36:54,456 --> 00:36:55,498
What are you doing here?

567
00:36:58,164 --> 00:36:59,331
- Hey, Samba!
- Yes?

568
00:36:59,414 --> 00:37:00,414
Didn't I tell you?

569
00:37:00,789 --> 00:37:01,831
That's Pani's daughter.

570
00:37:08,498 --> 00:37:09,539
Remember me?

571
00:37:09,873 --> 00:37:11,123
Well, you told me…

572
00:37:11,498 --> 00:37:15,206
"The name is Ramana. It will be of use
when you come to Guntur."

573
00:37:15,331 --> 00:37:16,789
That is why…

574
00:37:17,873 --> 00:37:18,831
Oh!

575
00:37:19,831 --> 00:37:21,331
- Hey, Yakobu!
- Sir?

576
00:37:21,789 --> 00:37:23,039
I'm beginning to blush.

577
00:37:24,998 --> 00:37:26,206
Go, bring three cups of tea.

578
00:37:30,331 --> 00:37:32,539
I refused to sign that day.
Did the old guy trouble this Pani guy…

579
00:37:34,998 --> 00:37:36,414
They must have tortured him.

580
00:37:36,748 --> 00:37:39,331
- He's not in the best situation, sir.
- Is he gone?

581
00:37:39,414 --> 00:37:40,539
Not yet, but…

582
00:37:41,164 --> 00:37:42,331
- Dear…
- Dad!

583
00:37:43,664 --> 00:37:45,456
Why do you make everyone cry?

584
00:37:47,039 --> 00:37:48,373
- Don't cry.
- Losing a job is okay.

585
00:37:48,456 --> 00:37:49,706
But if it costs me my life,

586
00:37:49,789 --> 00:37:51,831
should I laugh like a stand-up comedian
instead of crying?

587
00:37:51,998 --> 00:37:53,539
You can always find another job.

588
00:37:53,831 --> 00:37:55,081
Don't fret about it.

589
00:37:55,956 --> 00:37:59,414
Who will offer a job to a lawyer
ousted from the Law Minister's office?

590
00:38:01,623 --> 00:38:03,081
So, what do we do now?

591
00:38:06,498 --> 00:38:08,248
When she sneezes,
she turns more red.

592
00:38:09,373 --> 00:38:11,039
- Very tender.
- Yes.

593
00:38:11,498 --> 00:38:12,539
Where are you put up?

594
00:38:12,748 --> 00:38:13,914
Star Hotel.

595
00:38:14,289 --> 00:38:16,039
There are no-star hotels
around here!

596
00:38:16,164 --> 00:38:18,748
Star Hotel is just a name, sir.
It's actually a lodge.

597
00:38:18,831 --> 00:38:20,456
It's difficult to stay in lodges
for someone so ravishing.

598
00:38:23,373 --> 00:38:24,373
I was praising you.

599
00:38:26,706 --> 00:38:29,623
My dad's lost job, monthly EMIs…

600
00:38:29,873 --> 00:38:31,998
I can't handle this, Mr. Ramana.

601
00:38:35,539 --> 00:38:37,206
She's in distress.
Why are you crying?

602
00:38:37,289 --> 00:38:38,664
That's what I fail to understand, sir.

603
00:38:39,081 --> 00:38:40,873
I'm not even attached to her family.

604
00:38:41,164 --> 00:38:43,831
And yet, tears seem to flow in streams.

605
00:38:44,873 --> 00:38:47,498
The chili here is pungent.
His eyes must be burning.

606
00:38:47,581 --> 00:38:49,331
Oh! Makes sense.

607
00:39:06,373 --> 00:39:07,373
What is this?

608
00:39:07,831 --> 00:39:08,956
Just one signature.

609
00:39:15,998 --> 00:39:17,914
Do you know
what the old guy has written?

610
00:39:19,539 --> 00:39:21,789
I know, sir.
Actually, I was the one who drafted it.

611
00:39:22,748 --> 00:39:25,289
You should forget your mother.
Isn't that all?

612
00:39:26,081 --> 00:39:28,373
Like a boy going to a boarding school…

613
00:39:28,831 --> 00:39:31,706
I don't understand
why you have to act so dramatic!

614
00:39:33,664 --> 00:39:35,581
After all, your mother
had left you long ago.

615
00:39:36,039 --> 00:39:36,956
Don't you think?

616
00:39:51,081 --> 00:39:52,039
Hey!

617
00:39:52,581 --> 00:39:53,998
Did he tell you
why he didn't sell it to us?

618
00:39:54,289 --> 00:39:55,956
Some guy offered him a discount
of ten thousand rupees on each load.

619
00:39:56,664 --> 00:39:57,914
Did he say who?

620
00:39:58,081 --> 00:39:59,498
Go, have your lunch.

621
00:39:59,581 --> 00:40:01,831
Before you reach the last course,
he will spill all the beans.

622
00:40:02,081 --> 00:40:03,748
He has been buying red chili
from us for ten years now!

623
00:40:03,831 --> 00:40:06,039
When some guy offered you a discount…

624
00:40:06,164 --> 00:40:09,706
"Madam Bujji! I have this offer.
What shall I do?"

625
00:40:09,789 --> 00:40:12,539
Shouldn't you have asked me that?
Idiot! Don't let me hit you!

626
00:40:13,206 --> 00:40:14,914
You want to be consulted
about chili in the curry…

627
00:40:15,664 --> 00:40:17,539
as well as chili in the lorry.

628
00:40:17,748 --> 00:40:18,748
What is it?

629
00:40:18,831 --> 00:40:19,914
Nothing.

630
00:40:20,039 --> 00:40:22,331
You are playing my mouthpiece too.

631
00:40:22,414 --> 00:40:23,748
I just wanted
to play the listener this time.

632
00:40:24,539 --> 00:40:25,456
That's it.

633
00:40:27,456 --> 00:40:29,498
Why are you being so gentle,
Samba? A job half done!

634
00:40:30,706 --> 00:40:33,498
Hit him so hard that he divulges the name
of his mistress in front of his wife!

635
00:40:39,414 --> 00:40:40,373
Answer the call.

636
00:40:45,039 --> 00:40:46,998
This is the guy who stopped him
from buying chili from us.

637
00:40:47,164 --> 00:40:48,539
- Who is it?
- Hey!

638
00:40:49,164 --> 00:40:52,081
Touch him and I will see your end!

639
00:40:52,998 --> 00:40:54,081
You were saying something, Uncle?

640
00:40:54,414 --> 00:40:56,456
Stay there.

641
00:40:56,873 --> 00:40:59,289
If I don't come there in ten minutes
and burn you all up,

642
00:40:59,373 --> 00:41:00,581
I will change my name from Marx!

643
00:41:02,039 --> 00:41:05,123
Changing name and place at this age
on the Aadhar card and ration card

644
00:41:05,206 --> 00:41:06,248
is a big headache.

645
00:41:07,664 --> 00:41:08,539
Hey, Samba!

646
00:41:08,623 --> 00:41:09,539
Yes?

647
00:41:09,956 --> 00:41:11,081
Put him in the vehicle.

648
00:41:11,914 --> 00:41:13,456
Let's go and say hello to Uncle Marx.

649
00:41:21,914 --> 00:41:22,873
Uncle!

650
00:41:23,081 --> 00:41:25,623
You burned down our warehouse
and sent my dad to jail.

651
00:41:25,873 --> 00:41:27,123
You killed your elder brother.

652
00:41:27,206 --> 00:41:28,748
Don't panic. I got him.

653
00:41:29,039 --> 00:41:30,248
But you are still vengeful.

654
00:41:30,956 --> 00:41:32,706
That's why I have come to settle this
once and for all.

655
00:41:40,998 --> 00:41:43,206
The vehicle is here.
Where is the boy?

656
00:41:43,373 --> 00:41:45,581
Admit that it was wrong
to snatch our business.

657
00:41:46,123 --> 00:41:48,206
The boy himself will come to you jumping.

658
00:41:48,539 --> 00:41:49,414
Hey!

659
00:41:49,914 --> 00:41:52,498
Are you going to wait
until I fall at his feet?

660
00:41:52,581 --> 00:41:53,706
You morons!

661
00:41:54,831 --> 00:41:55,789
Right!

662
00:41:58,331 --> 00:41:59,206
Hey!

663
00:41:59,831 --> 00:42:01,789
You want to monopolize
the chili business?

664
00:42:02,039 --> 00:42:02,914
Why?

665
00:42:02,998 --> 00:42:05,123
Don't we have the load or a truck?

666
00:42:06,206 --> 00:42:09,581
Today Mr. Satyam is going to lose his son
in addition to his estranged wife.

667
00:42:14,289 --> 00:42:16,206
I want him at my feet.

668
00:42:17,873 --> 00:42:19,831
I will see how he will exit
from my compound.

669
00:42:37,081 --> 00:42:41,081
Hey! It is for me

670
00:42:41,331 --> 00:42:44,623
That you exist

671
00:42:44,873 --> 00:42:51,581
The sky above… nods in approval

672
00:42:52,831 --> 00:42:55,873
Drop the silence
At least a word will be welcome

673
00:42:55,956 --> 00:43:00,498
Hey, you blow my mind away!

674
00:43:02,123 --> 00:43:03,123
Come here.

675
00:43:03,331 --> 00:43:04,248
Come to this side.

676
00:43:04,914 --> 00:43:05,873
Hey!

677
00:43:13,873 --> 00:43:19,956
A warm desire enters my heart
And throws me off my feet

678
00:43:33,831 --> 00:43:34,706
Hey!

679
00:43:56,831 --> 00:44:00,914
Hey! It is for me

680
00:44:01,123 --> 00:44:04,414
That you exist

681
00:44:06,248 --> 00:44:12,498
The sky above… nods in approval

682
00:44:12,581 --> 00:44:15,664
Drop the silence
At least a word will be welcome

683
00:44:15,748 --> 00:44:20,164
Hey, you blow my mind away!

684
00:45:15,539 --> 00:45:17,414
Uncle, stop sitting around.

685
00:45:17,581 --> 00:45:18,664
Lie down. I will explain.

686
00:45:19,789 --> 00:45:21,123
Oh my God!

687
00:45:26,498 --> 00:45:27,456
Uncle!

688
00:45:28,414 --> 00:45:30,414
Something has been bothering me
since I came.

689
00:45:32,331 --> 00:45:34,373
Why have you put up a tent in winter?

690
00:45:35,456 --> 00:45:36,914
Well, it's your money and your pleasure.

691
00:45:37,331 --> 00:45:38,331
Bloody…

692
00:45:38,581 --> 00:45:40,498
Hey! Why are you walking away?

693
00:45:40,664 --> 00:45:42,623
His father has been
pestering me with calls.

694
00:45:42,706 --> 00:45:43,748
Where is he?

695
00:45:45,081 --> 00:45:46,373
Where the heck is he?

696
00:45:49,581 --> 00:45:50,539
Uncle!

697
00:45:51,289 --> 00:45:52,623
- Shut it!
- What?

698
00:46:38,831 --> 00:46:41,831
Our car was crushed under the shed.
A shard of tile landed on my head.

699
00:46:47,789 --> 00:46:48,914
Is your car insured?

700
00:46:49,373 --> 00:46:51,164
The mechanic is my guy.
He will get it ready in two days.

701
00:46:53,039 --> 00:46:54,081
What is your story, girl?

702
00:46:54,623 --> 00:46:56,206
Didn't you say it yourself

703
00:46:56,581 --> 00:46:59,164
that girls like me cannot stay in lodges?

704
00:46:59,914 --> 00:47:00,831
So…

705
00:47:00,956 --> 00:47:02,081
So…

706
00:47:02,456 --> 00:47:04,873
So? You walk in with your suitcases?

707
00:47:06,831 --> 00:47:08,123
There are no rooms here.

708
00:47:08,873 --> 00:47:09,873
Hey, come on.

709
00:47:13,373 --> 00:47:14,414
You are obedient.

710
00:47:15,289 --> 00:47:16,248
You will come up in life.

711
00:47:18,623 --> 00:47:19,498
Hey, girl.

712
00:47:20,623 --> 00:47:22,248
My aunt doesn't appreciate people
standing around.

713
00:47:23,623 --> 00:47:25,706
Go stay in the room under the staircase.

714
00:47:25,789 --> 00:47:27,123
- What?
- Yes.

715
00:47:27,289 --> 00:47:28,331
My clothes are there.

716
00:47:28,456 --> 00:47:30,081
Which room doesn't have your clothes?

717
00:47:30,206 --> 00:47:32,206
Burn them up
and half the problem will be solved.

718
00:47:32,289 --> 00:47:35,081
Sure, set them on fire. It's your
dad's money. She's got nothing to lose.

719
00:47:35,164 --> 00:47:36,248
He has given you a room. Go.

720
00:47:39,081 --> 00:47:40,081
Let's go.

721
00:47:45,581 --> 00:47:46,581
What is it?

722
00:47:46,873 --> 00:47:48,081
My accommodation?

723
00:47:48,164 --> 00:47:49,373
Your accommodation?

724
00:47:50,289 --> 00:47:51,873
- You are a man.
- Yes, sir.

725
00:47:51,956 --> 00:47:53,581
- You can stay anywhere.
- True.

726
00:47:54,373 --> 00:47:55,831
Make sure you don't enter the rooms.

727
00:47:56,581 --> 00:47:57,539
Sir?

728
00:47:57,998 --> 00:47:59,956
- This is your bedroom?
- Exactly!

729
00:48:00,289 --> 00:48:01,664
This is my balcony.

730
00:48:02,248 --> 00:48:03,456
What about the toilet?

731
00:48:04,331 --> 00:48:05,914
He said, "It's disgusting
to do it in the house.

732
00:48:05,998 --> 00:48:07,748
Do your business under some tree."

733
00:48:07,831 --> 00:48:09,123
- Who?
- Who else?

734
00:48:09,623 --> 00:48:10,956
My harasser, Ramana.

735
00:48:13,206 --> 00:48:14,623
How come she hasn't called me yet?

736
00:48:14,748 --> 00:48:16,414
Will she take it easy if I relax?

737
00:48:16,831 --> 00:48:17,831
Let's send her one.

738
00:48:19,748 --> 00:48:20,706
Is it your dad?

739
00:48:21,206 --> 00:48:22,248
What did he send?

740
00:48:24,664 --> 00:48:26,414
Does he want us to buy this from here?

741
00:48:26,539 --> 00:48:28,581
He says he will hang himself
if he doesn't get the signature.

742
00:48:28,664 --> 00:48:30,581
Cheap! He is not going to sign.

743
00:48:31,039 --> 00:48:33,373
He only fines people.
He never signs.

744
00:48:36,456 --> 00:48:37,623
Ramu…

745
00:48:39,539 --> 00:48:42,456
I tried to open the window,
but it's stuck.

746
00:48:42,664 --> 00:48:44,456
Can you please help?

747
00:48:51,331 --> 00:48:52,331
What did she say?

748
00:48:52,456 --> 00:48:53,956
- Something about the window--
- Hey…

749
00:48:54,581 --> 00:48:55,456
Before that.

750
00:48:55,831 --> 00:48:56,706
Ramu?

751
00:48:59,289 --> 00:49:02,289
I never realized
how good my name sounds!

752
00:49:02,414 --> 00:49:04,914
I never knew Ramana could be
shortened as Ramu, sir.

753
00:49:07,373 --> 00:49:08,331
Excuse me!

754
00:49:10,081 --> 00:49:11,206
Can I ask you something?

755
00:49:12,456 --> 00:49:13,414
You shouldn't mind.

756
00:49:17,331 --> 00:49:19,373
Do you rip your clothes
before putting them on or afterward?

757
00:49:19,456 --> 00:49:21,539
It's ripped jeans, Ramu.

758
00:49:21,664 --> 00:49:23,498
I guess they are more expensive
than regular jeans.

759
00:49:23,581 --> 00:49:24,456
How do you know, sir?

760
00:49:24,539 --> 00:49:26,998
I can tell from where
they are ripped and how much they show.

761
00:49:27,123 --> 00:49:28,581
They are a different category.

762
00:49:30,289 --> 00:49:31,456
Aren't they nice?

763
00:49:31,706 --> 00:49:32,914
You look phenomenal.

764
00:49:36,914 --> 00:49:37,831
Wow!

765
00:49:38,831 --> 00:49:41,164
What did I say about Pani's daughter?

766
00:49:41,414 --> 00:49:42,664
First, you said she's ravishing.

767
00:49:42,748 --> 00:49:44,456
Then you said
she's delightfully ravishing.

768
00:49:44,539 --> 00:49:45,748
She is not just delightful.

769
00:49:46,373 --> 00:49:47,706
She is bloody delightful.

770
00:49:47,873 --> 00:49:48,914
I will note that.

771
00:49:49,498 --> 00:49:51,539
- Did you put it to dry?
- Yes, I did.

772
00:49:51,831 --> 00:49:52,831
Did you eat yet?

773
00:49:53,206 --> 00:49:54,289
I wasn't offered.

774
00:49:54,373 --> 00:49:56,498
- Don't be shy in your own house.
- That's right.

775
00:49:56,581 --> 00:49:57,831
Go out and eat.

776
00:50:04,873 --> 00:50:05,789
What is this, dear?

777
00:50:05,873 --> 00:50:08,831
You became a minister
to make solid money,

778
00:50:08,956 --> 00:50:11,789
not to appoint a Commission
on the double murder

779
00:50:11,873 --> 00:50:13,956
that occurred in Renigunta
five years ago.

780
00:50:14,248 --> 00:50:18,123
You probably think Haridas is the same
old Das who partnered with your father.

781
00:50:18,331 --> 00:50:20,289
That was a tale of the past.

782
00:50:20,581 --> 00:50:25,039
Now you want to call me,
inquire, and throw me in jail?

783
00:50:25,539 --> 00:50:27,414
The state will be on fire.

784
00:50:27,623 --> 00:50:29,581
You want to call Das and inquire?

785
00:50:29,914 --> 00:50:33,206
Will the judge you have appointed
come to your office?

786
00:50:45,748 --> 00:50:46,748
Excuse me, ma'am.

787
00:50:48,498 --> 00:50:49,998
Judge Alok has messaged.

788
00:50:50,581 --> 00:50:53,623
Due to personal reasons, he has
withdrawn from the Hari Das Commission.

789
00:50:58,373 --> 00:50:59,456
Shocking!

790
00:51:04,039 --> 00:51:07,831
A judge can be replaced in a week.

791
00:51:08,539 --> 00:51:11,373
A minister can be replaced in ten days.

792
00:51:11,664 --> 00:51:16,039
But when Hari Das goes to prison,
it will take him twenty years to get out.

793
00:51:31,123 --> 00:51:32,831
Why mess with him?

794
00:51:33,748 --> 00:51:34,789
Listen to me.

795
00:51:35,998 --> 00:51:39,123
Even a vile person has some principles,
but he doesn't.

796
00:51:40,456 --> 00:51:41,914
He may not have principles…

797
00:51:42,581 --> 00:51:43,831
but I have responsibilities.

798
00:51:48,081 --> 00:51:49,539
- Narayana…
- Father-in-law?

799
00:51:50,373 --> 00:51:53,456
How did Das know that the judge
was going to come here?

800
00:51:53,539 --> 00:51:54,456
Why do you say that?

801
00:51:54,539 --> 00:51:56,873
We have appointed the Commission.
How would he not know?

802
00:51:56,956 --> 00:51:58,873
Not before we could announce.

803
00:51:59,206 --> 00:52:00,623
Kata Madhu must have told him.

804
00:52:00,748 --> 00:52:02,498
You can't relax in politics.

805
00:52:02,789 --> 00:52:04,123
Get your son ready.

806
00:52:04,498 --> 00:52:06,206
If his mother is in power, he'll be
an MP. Or else, an MLA.

807
00:52:08,706 --> 00:52:09,873
- Hey…
- Sir?

808
00:52:09,998 --> 00:52:11,081
What happened to the signature?

809
00:52:12,289 --> 00:52:14,373
It's not done yet, sir. I--

810
00:52:14,456 --> 00:52:16,248
- You…
- Sir!

811
00:52:33,789 --> 00:52:34,748
Hey, where to?

812
00:52:35,581 --> 00:52:37,956
There's no specific direction, sir.
Just going with the flow.

813
00:52:38,456 --> 00:52:40,248
Wear these glasses.
Let me see if they increase your glamour.

814
00:52:40,373 --> 00:52:41,289
Oh!

815
00:52:46,081 --> 00:52:47,539
- Great.
- Thank you, sir.

816
00:52:47,748 --> 00:52:48,748
Face sideways.

817
00:52:51,373 --> 00:52:52,289
Wow!

818
00:52:53,164 --> 00:52:54,456
You look smooth and shiny.

819
00:52:54,581 --> 00:52:55,581
I feel embarrassed, sir.

820
00:52:55,664 --> 00:52:56,623
So do I.

821
00:52:57,706 --> 00:52:59,289
Turn that way.
Don't change your posture.

822
00:53:02,623 --> 00:53:03,623
Coffee.

823
00:53:08,873 --> 00:53:10,206
You don't wear such clothes, do you?

824
00:53:12,789 --> 00:53:14,081
Not my style, cousin.

825
00:53:14,331 --> 00:53:15,706
You should learn.

826
00:53:16,664 --> 00:53:18,164
Don't just gift her
the half-sari you have…

827
00:53:18,623 --> 00:53:21,039
Those perfumes and creams…

828
00:53:21,123 --> 00:53:22,331
Don't remove them.

829
00:53:24,456 --> 00:53:25,414
Excuse me!

830
00:53:27,039 --> 00:53:28,956
Please groom her as well.

831
00:53:33,873 --> 00:53:35,331
If you don't mind,
can I say something?

832
00:53:36,456 --> 00:53:37,373
Sure.

833
00:53:37,456 --> 00:53:39,873
Your eyes are mesmerizing enough.

834
00:53:41,539 --> 00:53:43,289
Don't wear eyeliner and kohl.

835
00:53:43,706 --> 00:53:45,248
Stupid boys like me fall for you.

836
00:53:45,581 --> 00:53:47,206
Don't embarrass me, Ramu.

837
00:53:47,914 --> 00:53:50,623
Wow…

838
00:53:51,539 --> 00:53:54,664
Gosh, I never knew
there was so much melody in my name!

839
00:53:59,498 --> 00:54:00,789
What's with those sunglasses?

840
00:54:01,581 --> 00:54:03,164
You look like a pickpocket.
Take them off.

841
00:54:04,081 --> 00:54:05,248
You said they looked great earlier.

842
00:54:05,623 --> 00:54:06,706
She was here earlier.

843
00:54:12,331 --> 00:54:13,373
She won't return, I guess.

844
00:54:20,081 --> 00:54:23,331
If we ask him now, he would sign
with his blood instead of ink.

845
00:54:24,581 --> 00:54:26,123
Let's find the right time and get it.

846
00:54:26,248 --> 00:54:27,373
Yes!

847
00:54:32,081 --> 00:54:33,373
He started drinking!

848
00:54:33,456 --> 00:54:34,539
I can see it.

849
00:54:35,081 --> 00:54:35,956
Hi, sir!

850
00:54:36,289 --> 00:54:37,623
Why are you peeking like a thief?

851
00:54:37,706 --> 00:54:38,914
This is your private time, sir.

852
00:54:39,248 --> 00:54:40,873
Oh, wow. Can I join, sir?

853
00:54:41,164 --> 00:54:42,789
Is this some school to join?

854
00:54:43,289 --> 00:54:44,331
All you need is a glass.

855
00:54:44,414 --> 00:54:46,289
Well said, sir.
Thank you.

856
00:54:50,956 --> 00:54:52,206
All said and done…

857
00:54:52,998 --> 00:54:55,039
Her half-saris look more appealing on you.

858
00:54:57,456 --> 00:54:58,581
You look great.

859
00:54:58,831 --> 00:55:00,873
Is it scotch, sir?
I didn't expect this.

860
00:55:01,498 --> 00:55:04,206
Only the bottle is foreign.
The drink inside is local.

861
00:55:05,914 --> 00:55:07,248
Little. Just a little.

862
00:55:08,123 --> 00:55:09,289
- So, Balu…
- Sir?

863
00:55:10,998 --> 00:55:12,581
- That's enough.
- What is your full name?

864
00:55:13,248 --> 00:55:14,289
Bala Subramanyam, sir.

865
00:55:14,414 --> 00:55:15,956
- S.P.B?
- Just B.

866
00:55:17,623 --> 00:55:19,206
You are named after a legend.

867
00:55:19,289 --> 00:55:20,248
Thank you, sir.

868
00:55:20,706 --> 00:55:22,248
- With his inspiration…
- Sir…

869
00:55:23,539 --> 00:55:24,623
Sing a nice song.

870
00:55:25,248 --> 00:55:26,748
I have a problem with my shruti, sir.

871
00:55:26,831 --> 00:55:28,081
What do I care
if you have a problem with her?

872
00:55:28,164 --> 00:55:29,581
"Shruti" is not a person, sir.
It means tune.

873
00:55:29,664 --> 00:55:31,164
Is this Gurajada Kalamandir?

874
00:55:31,956 --> 00:55:32,998
It's just a warehouse.

875
00:55:33,873 --> 00:55:35,248
Forget about making mistakes.
You can try, come on.

876
00:55:35,331 --> 00:55:36,331
Okay, sir.

877
00:55:38,498 --> 00:55:39,706
Why are you looking at me like that?

878
00:55:41,748 --> 00:55:42,914
Would you like some beer?

879
00:55:43,164 --> 00:55:44,581
Sir, you are crossing a line there.

880
00:55:44,914 --> 00:55:47,664
Is this some Kabaddi match
to cross lines?

881
00:55:47,956 --> 00:55:48,998
She is a kid, sir.

882
00:55:49,123 --> 00:55:50,789
They fill the bars these days!

883
00:55:51,289 --> 00:55:52,956
Let's not touch on a controversial topic.

884
00:55:53,081 --> 00:55:54,039
Do you have vodka?

885
00:55:54,664 --> 00:55:56,206
Hey…

886
00:55:58,289 --> 00:56:00,456
- Soda or water?
- Juice.

887
00:56:00,956 --> 00:56:02,331
Health conscious, I see.

888
00:56:03,248 --> 00:56:04,623
- Hey, Yakobu.
- Sir.

889
00:56:10,164 --> 00:56:11,123
What is it?

890
00:56:13,331 --> 00:56:15,373
I carried her to school
in these arms, sir.

891
00:56:16,664 --> 00:56:18,748
- Take her to the bar tomorrow onwards.
- No way.

892
00:56:19,748 --> 00:56:21,414
Stop being dramatic and sing a song.

893
00:56:22,581 --> 00:56:24,081
Any specific pitch, sir?

894
00:56:24,248 --> 00:56:25,456
Any melody.

895
00:56:25,623 --> 00:56:26,623
Any melody.

896
00:56:27,414 --> 00:56:29,373
Why don't I sing the same song?
To hell with it.

897
00:56:32,248 --> 00:56:38,414
I'm drawn by some melody today

898
00:56:40,373 --> 00:56:45,956
To shake the past that lingers within

899
00:56:46,539 --> 00:56:51,123
Memories are sighs, memories are…

900
00:56:53,706 --> 00:56:55,623
I was singing a nice song, sir.
Why did you hit me?

901
00:56:55,706 --> 00:56:56,789
Soundarya…

902
00:56:59,081 --> 00:57:00,914
I feel like crying
when I think of her, Balu.

903
00:57:03,206 --> 00:57:04,664
May her great soul rest in peace.

904
00:57:05,623 --> 00:57:07,039
Sing a song of someone who's alive.

905
00:57:07,498 --> 00:57:08,748
Sing a happy song.

906
00:57:09,706 --> 00:57:11,581
Sing something that's
soothing and delightful.

907
00:57:12,748 --> 00:57:13,664
Idiot.

908
00:57:16,456 --> 00:57:17,539
This is the best for him.

909
00:57:22,414 --> 00:57:26,081
- Tell me, oh, cool breeze!
- Wow, what a song!

910
00:57:27,039 --> 00:57:29,998
- Embrace me with your chills
- Wow!

911
00:57:31,748 --> 00:57:33,206
How come I hear music with your song?

912
00:57:33,456 --> 00:57:34,748
I wasn't singing.
I played it on my phone.

913
00:57:34,873 --> 00:57:35,873
Wow!

914
00:57:36,081 --> 00:57:37,039
Play it.

915
00:57:37,248 --> 00:57:41,748
Tell me, oh, cool breeze
Embrace me with your chills

916
00:57:41,831 --> 00:57:45,331
Where the celebration of joy is

917
00:57:47,289 --> 00:57:50,706
Lead me there and tell me

918
00:57:51,831 --> 00:57:52,956
Bhumika!

919
00:57:54,664 --> 00:57:57,039
Wow! What a creation!

920
00:57:57,998 --> 00:57:59,623
Wow!

921
00:58:01,289 --> 00:58:02,373
He doesn't make them anymore.

922
00:58:03,581 --> 00:58:04,581
He has stopped.

923
00:58:05,539 --> 00:58:08,039
They barely have any flesh on them now.

924
00:58:09,331 --> 00:58:11,373
Hugging them is like
hugging yourself.

925
00:58:12,831 --> 00:58:14,831
We don't understand what they say.

926
00:58:15,164 --> 00:58:16,998
They don't understand what we say.

927
00:58:17,498 --> 00:58:19,206
They don't know how to play or to sway.

928
00:58:19,414 --> 00:58:20,789
Telugu, of course,
they would definitely not know.

929
00:58:24,498 --> 00:58:25,456
Baby…

930
00:58:32,831 --> 00:58:33,789
Phone.

931
00:59:07,706 --> 00:59:09,414
She looks like Prabhu Deva's dupe.

932
00:59:10,206 --> 00:59:11,706
Are there any bones in her body or not?

933
00:59:11,789 --> 00:59:13,873
Forget about her body.
Where is the cigarette, sir?

934
00:59:20,414 --> 00:59:21,748
Updated piece.

935
00:59:22,998 --> 00:59:24,039
- Balu.
- Baby?

936
00:59:24,498 --> 00:59:25,623
Go to my library.

937
00:59:26,456 --> 00:59:28,039
- Play song fifteen.
- Done.

938
00:59:41,623 --> 00:59:42,748
Volume at twenty.

939
00:59:55,956 --> 00:59:56,831
Hey!

940
01:00:01,581 --> 01:00:02,498
Hey!

941
01:00:13,581 --> 01:00:18,289
Check if it has fallen close by
My gold necklace

942
01:00:18,789 --> 01:00:23,998
Check if it has fallen near you
My gold necklace

943
01:00:24,414 --> 01:00:29,706
Check if it has fallen close by
My gold necklace

944
01:00:30,081 --> 01:00:35,289
Check if it has fallen near you
My gold necklace

945
01:00:58,664 --> 01:00:59,539
Sorry, sir.

946
01:01:01,123 --> 01:01:02,289
Why was my lungi snatched?

947
01:01:02,373 --> 01:01:04,206
Probably she got too carried away
by the dance, sir.

948
01:01:04,289 --> 01:01:05,748
- What dance was that?
- Right, sir.

949
01:01:06,456 --> 01:01:07,956
You have brought Prabhu Deva's dupe.

950
01:01:08,539 --> 01:01:10,414
Whoa!

951
01:01:11,248 --> 01:01:12,748
I couldn't match her energy.

952
01:01:13,456 --> 01:01:15,123
I haven't danced like this
in my entire career.

953
01:01:16,664 --> 01:01:17,581
My goodness.

954
01:01:19,373 --> 01:01:20,581
Whatever you say…

955
01:01:21,789 --> 01:01:22,914
I have enjoyed a lot, man.

956
01:01:23,039 --> 01:01:24,081
Same here, sir.

957
01:01:24,206 --> 01:01:26,164
Life is all about small moments
like these.

958
01:01:26,289 --> 01:01:27,164
True, sir.

959
01:01:32,456 --> 01:01:33,873
Why are you pulling a pen
out of your blouse?

960
01:01:35,914 --> 01:01:37,206
Why are you pulling out a paper
from your pocket?

961
01:01:37,914 --> 01:01:41,706
This small moment calls for
a scribble of your initials, sir.

962
01:01:41,914 --> 01:01:43,498
So, you didn't come here
for entertainment?

963
01:01:46,664 --> 01:01:47,873
You clearly have an agenda.

964
01:01:49,789 --> 01:01:51,373
Hold this for me, please.

965
01:01:56,748 --> 01:01:57,748
Slowly.

966
01:01:57,998 --> 01:02:00,081
He was drunk last night
and spared you with a slap.

967
01:02:00,956 --> 01:02:03,248
If he sees us when he gets sober,
he will kill us, Balu.

968
01:02:03,748 --> 01:02:05,373
- Thank God!
- Let's sneak out before he wakes up.

969
01:02:05,456 --> 01:02:06,998
- Let's go.
- We won't ever see him again.

970
01:02:07,206 --> 01:02:08,623
It should just remain a dream.

971
01:02:08,706 --> 01:02:09,581
- The garage is that way.
- Yes.

972
01:02:11,539 --> 01:02:12,748
Here's the money.
Is the car ready?

973
01:02:13,081 --> 01:02:14,289
The headlight isn't working.

974
01:02:14,373 --> 01:02:15,414
We'll reach there
before we'd need to turn them on.

975
01:02:15,789 --> 01:02:16,998
The brakes aren't working either.

976
01:02:17,081 --> 01:02:18,248
- We won't use them.
- That's the spirit.

977
01:02:18,331 --> 01:02:19,914
- Keys, sir!
- Give it here!

978
01:02:20,164 --> 01:02:21,289
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

979
01:02:24,373 --> 01:02:25,789
No looking back!

980
01:02:33,998 --> 01:02:36,081
- What is that?
- Looks like some statue.

981
01:02:36,331 --> 01:02:37,248
Whose?

982
01:02:37,331 --> 01:02:39,414
Who is the scoundrel
that knocked down my father's statue?

983
01:02:40,289 --> 01:02:41,289
Hey, come on.

984
01:02:41,373 --> 01:02:43,081
They are Royal Satyam's guests, brother.

985
01:02:43,164 --> 01:02:44,789
Satyam killed my father!

986
01:02:44,956 --> 01:02:47,206
Now, his guests won't even
spare his statue!

987
01:02:47,456 --> 01:02:48,414
Get them!

988
01:02:49,039 --> 01:02:50,998
Sir, it's a mistake.
It was an accident.

989
01:02:51,456 --> 01:02:52,914
Tell us if you want money.
Madam can give you.

990
01:02:52,998 --> 01:02:53,914
Who wants your money?

991
01:02:53,998 --> 01:02:55,373
So, what do you expect from us?

992
01:02:55,456 --> 01:02:58,498
You better fix the head of the statue,
or I will replace it with yours!

993
01:02:58,664 --> 01:03:00,748
- Hey, pull them out! Get them!
- I'm not a great artist, sir!

994
01:03:00,873 --> 01:03:02,623
- Get them out. Shut up!
- Sir! Hey!

995
01:03:02,706 --> 01:03:04,289
Hey, please! Please, brother.

996
01:03:04,373 --> 01:03:05,789
Oh, brother!

997
01:03:10,164 --> 01:03:11,039
Sir…

998
01:03:17,331 --> 01:03:18,998
- Get her!
- Sir!

999
01:03:19,623 --> 01:03:20,664
Please ask them to stop, sir.

1000
01:03:20,748 --> 01:03:22,081
We offered them money
and they still won't listen.

1001
01:03:22,164 --> 01:03:23,581
Is he some Ambedkar or Gandhi?

1002
01:03:26,998 --> 01:03:27,914
My elder brother.

1003
01:03:29,623 --> 01:03:31,873
I will pawn my head if need be,
but I will get the statue redone.

1004
01:03:35,206 --> 01:03:36,289
Not this head, sir. My head.

1005
01:03:43,206 --> 01:03:45,581
Why discuss it with her, Uncle?
Let's tie her up!

1006
01:03:45,706 --> 01:03:46,998
Please don't harm her, sir!

1007
01:04:11,998 --> 01:04:13,706
What is this brute force against women?

1008
01:04:14,248 --> 01:04:16,206
- Against women, really? Idiot!
- Hey!

1009
01:04:16,998 --> 01:04:19,248
Let him go.
They have done something wrong.

1010
01:04:19,373 --> 01:04:20,748
As if he has done some engineering!

1011
01:04:20,956 --> 01:04:22,956
An offender shall be punished.

1012
01:04:23,123 --> 01:04:24,039
Oh, my!

1013
01:04:25,956 --> 01:04:28,248
Uncle, please don't act
like Rajinikanth in Pedarayudu.

1014
01:04:28,331 --> 01:04:29,414
It doesn't suit you.

1015
01:04:29,581 --> 01:04:31,706
- Limit the issue to the statue.
- Is it so?

1016
01:04:32,539 --> 01:04:34,456
I heard this statue
is a jinx to our village.

1017
01:04:35,039 --> 01:04:36,206
When people look at it during the day,
they meet with failure.

1018
01:04:36,289 --> 01:04:37,873
If they look at it at night,
they cannot get a wink of sleep.

1019
01:04:38,206 --> 01:04:40,081
- Why don't you tell him, guys?
- He doesn't listen, you know.

1020
01:04:40,206 --> 01:04:42,289
Hey, what are you just watching
and not beating him up?

1021
01:04:42,664 --> 01:04:43,539
Hey!

1022
01:04:45,498 --> 01:04:48,581
If anyone steps forward,
I will twist this idiot's arm so much,

1023
01:04:48,664 --> 01:04:50,081
- it will get dislodged from the groove.
- Hey…

1024
01:04:50,539 --> 01:04:52,789
Hey, don't come forward!
He will break my arm.

1025
01:04:52,873 --> 01:04:54,539
- Hey, don't come.
- Hey, let go of him.

1026
01:05:00,373 --> 01:05:01,456
- Hey, Balu!
- Sir.

1027
01:05:01,664 --> 01:05:02,789
Go sit in the car first.

1028
01:05:03,664 --> 01:05:05,081
Come. Ammu, come.

1029
01:05:22,914 --> 01:05:24,456
- Call me once the car is ready.
- Sure, sir.

1030
01:05:24,539 --> 01:05:25,498
I will GPay you.

1031
01:06:02,289 --> 01:06:05,956
The sugar cube in my coffee cup is you
It's you

1032
01:06:06,456 --> 01:06:10,081
The tracery of kohl around my eyes is you
It's you

1033
01:06:10,623 --> 01:06:14,581
The blush of chrysanthemum on my cheeks
Is you, it's you

1034
01:06:14,789 --> 01:06:18,331
You wrap around my breath like perfume

1035
01:06:18,498 --> 01:06:22,706
Oh, my baby!
I want to pinch your cheeks

1036
01:06:22,789 --> 01:06:26,873
Oh, my baby!
I want to kiss you many times

1037
01:06:26,998 --> 01:06:31,914
Oh, my baby!
With my stole, let me make you a tie

1038
01:06:40,164 --> 01:06:44,248
Craving, craving, craving for you
The novel next to my pillow is you

1039
01:06:44,414 --> 01:06:48,081
Tripping, tripping, tripping on you
My new playlist is now just you

1040
01:06:48,581 --> 01:06:52,581
Craving, craving, craving for you
The novel next to my pillow is you

1041
01:06:52,748 --> 01:06:56,539
Tripping, tripping, tripping on you
My new playlist is now just you

1042
01:07:06,956 --> 01:07:07,831
Hey, Balu.

1043
01:07:21,581 --> 01:07:25,581
You are the sun who is my wake-up call
With his warm touch

1044
01:07:25,748 --> 01:07:29,748
You are the full moon
Jumping over my balcony walls

1045
01:07:29,914 --> 01:07:33,998
You are the one among millions
Born only for me

1046
01:07:34,123 --> 01:07:37,873
I became your wife in secret
As soon as I opened my eyes

1047
01:07:37,956 --> 01:07:41,998
Oh, my baby!
I want to lie next to you

1048
01:07:42,123 --> 01:07:46,123
Oh, my baby!
I want to watch the stars with you

1049
01:07:46,289 --> 01:07:51,164
Oh, my baby!
I want to fill the space in your embrace

1050
01:07:55,331 --> 01:07:59,498
Craving, craving, craving for you
The novel next to my pillow is you

1051
01:07:59,581 --> 01:08:03,373
Tripping, tripping, tripping on you
My new playlist is now just you

1052
01:08:03,706 --> 01:08:07,831
Craving, craving, craving for you
The novel next to my pillow is you

1053
01:08:07,914 --> 01:08:11,206
Tripping, tripping, tripping on you
My new playlist is now just you

1054
01:08:11,373 --> 01:08:15,081
Oh, my baby!

1055
01:08:15,414 --> 01:08:18,956
Oh, my baby!

1056
01:08:19,539 --> 01:08:22,206
Oh, my baby!

1057
01:08:23,956 --> 01:08:26,206
Oh, my baby!

1058
01:08:47,414 --> 01:08:48,873
Ramana is heading back.

1059
01:08:49,539 --> 01:08:50,414
Some other time.

1060
01:08:52,206 --> 01:08:53,081
Excuse me!

1061
01:08:55,414 --> 01:08:57,831
Ask your mom to ward off the evil eye.

1062
01:08:59,581 --> 01:09:01,539
You look gorgeous in peach.

1063
01:09:09,456 --> 01:09:10,748
How come you have become so thin?

1064
01:09:10,831 --> 01:09:12,789
- They don't serve rice in Guntur.
- Really?

1065
01:09:12,914 --> 01:09:14,331
I wonder what they served instead.

1066
01:09:20,081 --> 01:09:21,539
Sir, the girl has returned
and he has left.

1067
01:09:22,289 --> 01:09:23,164
Sir.

1068
01:09:23,664 --> 01:09:24,623
What is this, sir?

1069
01:09:24,789 --> 01:09:26,289
You call yourself a lawyer,
but where is your clarity?

1070
01:09:26,706 --> 01:09:28,873
When you say "The girl has returned",
do you mean the neighbor or your maid?

1071
01:09:28,956 --> 01:09:30,581
"My daughter has returned."
That's clarity.

1072
01:09:30,664 --> 01:09:32,748
Where did she come back from?
From a different city.

1073
01:09:33,039 --> 01:09:34,789
Who dropped her off?
Ramana dropped her off.

1074
01:09:34,873 --> 01:09:35,789
More clarity.

1075
01:09:35,914 --> 01:09:36,789
Did he come inside?

1076
01:09:36,956 --> 01:09:40,414
Since we don't offer any pleasantries,
he took a U-turn and left.

1077
01:09:40,498 --> 01:09:41,664
Utmost clarity.

1078
01:09:41,748 --> 01:09:43,498
You know how relieving
this narrative is, sir?

1079
01:09:43,706 --> 01:09:44,748
Who am I talking to?

1080
01:09:44,873 --> 01:09:46,331
- I don't need clarity on that--
- Hey, listen!

1081
01:09:46,998 --> 01:09:48,039
I'm talking to Mr. Venkata Swamy.

1082
01:09:48,289 --> 01:09:49,331
Why am I talking to him?

1083
01:09:49,539 --> 01:09:50,789
To get Ramana arrested.

1084
01:09:52,123 --> 01:09:53,456
This is what you call clarity.

1085
01:09:53,873 --> 01:09:55,956
Why should he be arrested?
Don't we need clarity on that matter?

1086
01:09:56,039 --> 01:09:57,081
You don't need that clarity.

1087
01:10:21,664 --> 01:10:23,081
Why are you blocking the road?

1088
01:10:26,081 --> 01:10:27,123
Have you lost your way?

1089
01:10:46,081 --> 01:10:48,206
Bhogineni Veera Venkata Ramana.

1090
01:10:50,039 --> 01:10:51,039
What's your full name, chap?

1091
01:10:55,414 --> 01:10:57,914
You can't call me "chap"
just because you can wag your tongue.

1092
01:10:58,956 --> 01:11:00,789
My arm will start acting then.

1093
01:11:01,331 --> 01:11:02,873
I don't know which way I might twist it.

1094
01:11:03,206 --> 01:11:04,289
What can you twist?

1095
01:11:04,956 --> 01:11:07,831
There's a case against you for throwing
a tantrum at Mr. Vyra Venkata Swamy.

1096
01:11:10,206 --> 01:11:12,373
- You mean the brawl at the party office?
- At home.

1097
01:11:16,248 --> 01:11:17,789
How much did you charge the old man?

1098
01:11:18,206 --> 01:11:19,664
Don't cross the line.

1099
01:11:20,164 --> 01:11:22,206
Is this your first time
at the police station?

1100
01:11:22,873 --> 01:11:25,123
I'm not an employee like you
to come here regularly.

1101
01:11:29,331 --> 01:11:30,373
How dare you…

1102
01:11:31,873 --> 01:11:32,748
Let go of my hand.

1103
01:11:34,373 --> 01:11:35,789
I will flay you, bloody fool!

1104
01:11:36,123 --> 01:11:37,456
Let him remove his uniform.

1105
01:11:38,206 --> 01:11:39,831
I will break this rogue's leg!

1106
01:11:40,706 --> 01:11:42,664
What makes you so arrogant?

1107
01:11:43,164 --> 01:11:44,039
Arrogant?

1108
01:11:45,123 --> 01:11:46,956
I don't get arrogant
from others' strength, Uncle.

1109
01:11:47,331 --> 01:11:48,456
I am like Chiranjeevi.

1110
01:11:48,914 --> 01:11:49,873
Self-made!

1111
01:11:50,456 --> 01:11:52,331
Let's put you behind bars
for a week and polish you.

1112
01:11:52,664 --> 01:11:53,873
We will know what type you are!

1113
01:11:54,456 --> 01:11:56,748
Am I some brass vessel
that he wants to polish me?

1114
01:11:58,539 --> 01:12:01,206
Some useless idiot
will come with bail for me.

1115
01:12:02,039 --> 01:12:04,414
We will discuss more on polishing
or getting polished.

1116
01:12:05,498 --> 01:12:07,123
- Sir?
- Hey, Balu!

1117
01:12:07,498 --> 01:12:09,998
I just said "Some useless idiot",
and you walked in! What timing!

1118
01:12:10,081 --> 01:12:11,039
I have got you bail, sir.

1119
01:12:11,789 --> 01:12:13,081
- You have got me bail?
- Yes, sir.

1120
01:12:13,164 --> 01:12:14,039
Why?

1121
01:12:14,789 --> 01:12:17,248
Actually, sir, during my journey with you…

1122
01:12:17,331 --> 01:12:18,206
During your journey?

1123
01:12:19,914 --> 01:12:21,914
- Don't say it and kill my feelings.
- Okay, sir.

1124
01:12:22,331 --> 01:12:25,623
Your boss files a case, and you
submit bail. Is this your side hustle?

1125
01:12:25,789 --> 01:12:27,456
Look who's talking about side hustle!

1126
01:12:27,873 --> 01:12:29,998
- Pani filed this case?
- Yes, sir.

1127
01:12:30,664 --> 01:12:31,623
What have I done according to him?

1128
01:12:31,748 --> 01:12:32,789
They have written all lies.

1129
01:12:36,789 --> 01:12:37,873
Why don't we make it real?

1130
01:13:04,789 --> 01:13:06,414
- Well, Pani…
- Sir?

1131
01:13:07,206 --> 01:13:12,289
Why did your junior choose a losing case
for his first assignment?

1132
01:13:14,831 --> 01:13:15,914
Hey, Mr. Spicy Pepper!

1133
01:13:16,748 --> 01:13:17,623
You…

1134
01:13:18,914 --> 01:13:20,789
In a powerful household like ours…

1135
01:13:21,456 --> 01:13:23,164
One son is a blessing.

1136
01:13:24,039 --> 01:13:25,498
Two is a problem.

1137
01:13:26,539 --> 01:13:28,956
If the second one turns out
to be like you, it's disgusting.

1138
01:13:29,456 --> 01:13:31,706
- Sir, actually--
- I'm old. I might forget.

1139
01:13:31,873 --> 01:13:32,748
Let me finish.

1140
01:13:35,039 --> 01:13:39,331
Kids leave their parents
in old age homes these days.

1141
01:13:39,748 --> 01:13:42,914
Why did you drive so far
to meet your mother?

1142
01:13:45,873 --> 01:13:47,039
Get those papers.

1143
01:13:47,456 --> 01:13:48,331
Listen!

1144
01:13:49,498 --> 01:13:50,956
The papers are here.

1145
01:13:51,706 --> 01:13:53,373
The case is in the court.

1146
01:13:53,998 --> 01:13:55,039
It's a false case, of course.

1147
01:13:55,164 --> 01:13:58,373
If you choose a fight, prepare a counter
and go to court.

1148
01:13:58,539 --> 01:14:01,123
If you choose peace,
sign the papers and go home.

1149
01:14:03,081 --> 01:14:04,039
- Balu.
- Sir.

1150
01:14:09,831 --> 01:14:11,123
You wrote the FIR, didn't you?

1151
01:14:12,831 --> 01:14:14,206
Read it without spelling mistakes.

1152
01:14:25,331 --> 01:14:27,206
"18th August 2023.

1153
01:14:27,373 --> 01:14:29,664
Jubilee Hills Police Station,
Jubilee Hills, Hyderabad.

1154
01:14:30,456 --> 01:14:31,623
To the Inspector.

1155
01:14:32,331 --> 01:14:33,206
Sir,

1156
01:14:33,539 --> 01:14:36,289
I, Vyra Venkata Swamy, am a
former Member of the Legislative Assembly

1157
01:14:36,373 --> 01:14:39,206
and former Minister, aged 80."

1158
01:14:39,623 --> 01:14:40,498
Sir…

1159
01:14:40,831 --> 01:14:45,623
"A resident of Guntur, Veera Venkata
Ramana, son of Bhogineni Satyanarayana,

1160
01:14:45,706 --> 01:14:50,873
alias Royal Satyam, forcefully entered
my house around 10:20 a.m., today.

1161
01:14:51,081 --> 01:14:54,373
He broke my eighty-five-inch,
fully smart Samsung TV…

1162
01:14:54,873 --> 01:14:57,789
using the ashtray from the center table.

1163
01:14:58,914 --> 01:15:00,123
He smashed it into pieces."

1164
01:15:01,414 --> 01:15:02,289
Hey!

1165
01:15:07,789 --> 01:15:08,748
Hey, what is it?

1166
01:15:10,289 --> 01:15:11,164
Hey!

1167
01:15:14,289 --> 01:15:15,289
Hey!

1168
01:15:22,581 --> 01:15:25,456
"Throwing out an Italian marble-made
dining table chair…"

1169
01:15:26,123 --> 01:15:27,248
Pani, don't stop.

1170
01:15:27,373 --> 01:15:30,873
"He picked up the expensive Chinaware and
smashed it against the floor and walls.

1171
01:15:34,414 --> 01:15:37,498
He threw the Italian silverware
and food kept for guests

1172
01:15:37,581 --> 01:15:39,664
onto the ground
without any discrimination.

1173
01:15:42,581 --> 01:15:45,123
He destroyed the cupboard
in the dining hall, along with…

1174
01:15:45,831 --> 01:15:47,706
with the items inside!

1175
01:15:55,664 --> 01:15:58,873
He recklessly beat up the security
on duty who tried to stop him

1176
01:15:58,998 --> 01:16:00,956
and intimidated everyone.

1177
01:16:21,539 --> 01:16:24,206
Attacking my son-in-law,
Mr. Pakka Narayana,

1178
01:16:24,289 --> 01:16:26,373
and unmindful of his age,
disrespectfully slapped him."

1179
01:16:43,039 --> 01:16:44,289
- Pani!
- Yes.

1180
01:16:44,498 --> 01:16:48,831
"The most expensive chandelier
I acquired from Belgium 25 years ago…

1181
01:16:49,914 --> 01:16:52,289
- despite my repeated appeals…
- Hey! No…

1182
01:16:52,581 --> 01:16:53,498
Hey!

1183
01:16:53,748 --> 01:16:56,039
- was brutally pulled down."
- Stop!

1184
01:16:56,289 --> 01:16:57,164
Hey!

1185
01:17:53,623 --> 01:17:54,956
Where did they raise you?

1186
01:17:56,373 --> 01:17:58,039
In their house
or on the streets of Guntur?

1187
01:18:01,998 --> 01:18:03,748
Anyway, what is there
to discuss with him, Dad?

1188
01:18:04,248 --> 01:18:05,331
What does he want?

1189
01:18:07,123 --> 01:18:08,039
Property?

1190
01:18:09,623 --> 01:18:11,456
Talk to Pani and take whatever you want.

1191
01:18:13,164 --> 01:18:15,498
If you throw a stone at a tree,
you might get some fruit.

1192
01:18:16,206 --> 01:18:18,331
If you throw a stone into a mire,
what will you possibly get?

1193
01:18:21,414 --> 01:18:23,414
Clear the trash in ten minutes.

1194
01:18:42,539 --> 01:18:43,498
Pani…

1195
01:18:44,498 --> 01:18:45,373
give me the papers.

1196
01:19:09,456 --> 01:19:12,248
Hunger remains unsatisfied
unless the mother herself serves you.

1197
01:19:12,581 --> 01:19:13,539
It's a proverb.

1198
01:19:16,081 --> 01:19:17,873
Don't forget to read the last line, Pani.

1199
01:19:18,706 --> 01:19:22,664
"The golden-framed photograph gifted by
the members of the Raichur Constituency

1200
01:19:22,748 --> 01:19:24,873
has also been destroyed by him.

1201
01:19:27,789 --> 01:19:30,664
Witnesses for this incident are
Basavaraju Sarangapani, B.A, B.L,

1202
01:19:30,873 --> 01:19:32,289
and Basavaraju Amukta Malyada."

1203
01:20:00,248 --> 01:20:01,914
Ramu, I'm really sorry.

1204
01:20:02,039 --> 01:20:02,914
Why?

1205
01:20:03,664 --> 01:20:05,706
Actually, the reason I signed--

1206
01:20:05,789 --> 01:20:06,831
You lied for your father.

1207
01:20:07,956 --> 01:20:09,164
Why should you tell the truth for me?

1208
01:20:12,289 --> 01:20:13,539
You remembered me in Guntur.

1209
01:20:14,873 --> 01:20:15,914
And you sidelined me in the city.

1210
01:20:17,248 --> 01:20:18,123
You are justified.

1211
01:20:23,706 --> 01:20:24,914
Why did she ask me who raised me?

1212
01:20:26,498 --> 01:20:27,706
Ideally, she should have raised me.

1213
01:20:28,956 --> 01:20:31,248
But you told me it's a love story
between you and your mom, sir.

1214
01:20:31,331 --> 01:20:32,289
Love, my foot!

1215
01:20:33,456 --> 01:20:36,664
The way she glared down
and said, "Clear the trash!"

1216
01:20:37,164 --> 01:20:38,039
Did you see that?

1217
01:20:41,414 --> 01:20:42,581
Who do you think the trash was?

1218
01:20:43,581 --> 01:20:44,456
It was me.

1219
01:20:46,206 --> 01:20:48,789
Did you think she meant
the broken glass and porcelain?

1220
01:20:52,873 --> 01:20:54,706
My mother, who should have hit me
when I was a kid,

1221
01:20:55,456 --> 01:20:58,831
now invites me over
and slaps me in all dignity.

1222
01:21:01,956 --> 01:21:02,831
This chap, Ramana…

1223
01:21:04,623 --> 01:21:05,998
His life is a miracle!

1224
01:21:07,914 --> 01:21:09,539
His mother doesn't want him.
His father doesn't remember him.

1225
01:21:15,581 --> 01:21:16,748
On the outside, it's fair and lovely.

1226
01:21:17,456 --> 01:21:19,123
Deep inside, it's all unfair and lonely.

1227
01:21:31,831 --> 01:21:32,706
Doesn't light up.

1228
01:21:33,873 --> 01:21:34,789
Just like my life.

1229
01:21:50,789 --> 01:21:53,873
SHRI KANAKADURGA CHILI YARD

1230
01:22:01,623 --> 01:22:03,456
Cousin, some Kata Madhu waiting.

1231
01:22:03,581 --> 01:22:04,664
He says he doesn't get along
with your grandfather.

1232
01:22:07,206 --> 01:22:08,248
What does he want?

1233
01:22:08,539 --> 01:22:09,873
I heard they slapped
a false case against you,

1234
01:22:09,956 --> 01:22:11,998
beat you up, and coerced you to sign.

1235
01:22:13,039 --> 01:22:14,373
Are we living in a community or a jungle?

1236
01:22:15,331 --> 01:22:16,789
Do they think there's no one
to question them?

1237
01:22:18,289 --> 01:22:20,539
I will make you contest against her.

1238
01:22:20,748 --> 01:22:22,081
I will spend a hundred crores
if necessary.

1239
01:22:22,414 --> 01:22:23,748
I will send you to the Assembly.

1240
01:22:23,956 --> 01:22:25,164
All that is fine, boss.

1241
01:22:26,039 --> 01:22:27,498
How do you know about this?

1242
01:22:27,789 --> 01:22:31,123
Because their driver is on my payroll.

1243
01:22:31,206 --> 01:22:32,081
Really?

1244
01:22:34,331 --> 01:22:35,623
- Hey, Samba.
- Yes?

1245
01:22:36,706 --> 01:22:38,039
I want to have a heart-to-heart
conversation with this gentleman.

1246
01:22:38,331 --> 01:22:39,206
Close the shutter.

1247
01:22:39,289 --> 01:22:41,456
Why should your grandfather
be the only one to rule?

1248
01:22:42,539 --> 01:22:43,998
I just wanted to meet my mom…

1249
01:22:44,914 --> 01:22:46,248
not win against her.

1250
01:23:03,373 --> 01:23:06,956
Son, please let go of me.
Please don't kill me.

1251
01:23:07,206 --> 01:23:08,081
That boy…

1252
01:23:08,998 --> 01:23:13,081
The first emotion I had
when I saw Ramana was pity.

1253
01:23:13,539 --> 01:23:17,206
I asked him, "I want to make you contest
against your mother. What do you feel?"

1254
01:23:17,539 --> 01:23:19,039
He almost hugged me.

1255
01:23:19,289 --> 01:23:21,539
Trust me, I couldn't even breathe!

1256
01:23:21,623 --> 01:23:23,456
I wanted to leave,
but he wouldn't let me.

1257
01:23:24,248 --> 01:23:25,373
He was holding my feet.

1258
01:23:25,623 --> 01:23:27,539
I asked him if he had any proof.

1259
01:23:27,706 --> 01:23:29,748
That's it.
He immediately went home

1260
01:23:29,831 --> 01:23:32,623
and got me a family picture
from a treasured box.

1261
01:23:35,206 --> 01:23:36,248
Venkata Swamy!

1262
01:23:36,998 --> 01:23:38,164
I have only one thing to say.

1263
01:23:38,873 --> 01:23:41,164
Your grandson or this one?

1264
01:23:41,998 --> 01:23:44,789
If you ask us to choose between
Raja Gopal or Venkata Ramana…

1265
01:23:45,164 --> 01:23:47,289
we stand with Venkata Ramana.

1266
01:23:48,123 --> 01:23:49,331
You better understand this.

1267
01:23:49,539 --> 01:23:52,539
Otherwise… the public
will make you realize.

1268
01:23:55,873 --> 01:23:58,789
Unlike his dad, he doesn't sit
at home behind closed doors.

1269
01:23:59,039 --> 01:24:01,456
He barges into our house
breaking open all doors.

1270
01:24:01,581 --> 01:24:03,956
Because that is Royal Satyam.

1271
01:24:04,498 --> 01:24:05,498
He's black and white.

1272
01:24:05,831 --> 01:24:09,039
And this is Rowdy Ramana,
a 70mm cinema scope.

1273
01:24:09,623 --> 01:24:10,581
Right, sir.

1274
01:24:10,664 --> 01:24:13,748
If he comes before the public and speaks,
Janadalam won't even get the deposits.

1275
01:24:16,956 --> 01:24:19,289
He is a truck without brakes.

1276
01:24:19,664 --> 01:24:20,789
Who can stop him?

1277
01:24:30,164 --> 01:24:31,248
The cops are here.

1278
01:24:32,581 --> 01:24:33,498
Sir…

1279
01:24:33,789 --> 01:24:35,414
They are the most prominent family
in this area, sir.

1280
01:24:36,581 --> 01:24:38,873
Please approach with caution, sir.

1281
01:24:38,956 --> 01:24:40,248
I mean, with love.

1282
01:24:48,498 --> 01:24:49,498
Ma'am?

1283
01:24:53,039 --> 01:24:55,498
Dussehra is over.
We even gave donations, didn't we?

1284
01:24:55,623 --> 01:24:57,498
She's just a kid, sir.
I will make her understand.

1285
01:24:57,664 --> 01:24:59,081
Sir has come from Hyderabad.

1286
01:24:59,414 --> 01:25:01,373
It's shocking how people have started
traveling so far for donations!

1287
01:25:01,581 --> 01:25:03,331
Hey! Don't you get derisive!

1288
01:25:03,998 --> 01:25:05,164
Donations? Again?!

1289
01:25:05,623 --> 01:25:06,748
How many times should we give?

1290
01:25:07,164 --> 01:25:08,289
Come back next year. Leave!

1291
01:25:08,498 --> 01:25:11,623
Hey, don't infuriate me!
I will lock you all up!

1292
01:25:11,706 --> 01:25:14,039
What? For donations?
Sure, try me!

1293
01:25:14,123 --> 01:25:15,539
Hey, hold up.
Just wait.

1294
01:25:16,248 --> 01:25:18,039
- What is the issue?
- There is no issue.

1295
01:25:18,456 --> 01:25:20,164
If Venkata Ramana comes,
we need to go to Hyderabad.

1296
01:25:20,331 --> 01:25:22,123
If you don't know the way,
we can send someone to guide you.

1297
01:25:22,331 --> 01:25:23,456
Why do you want Ramana?

1298
01:25:24,248 --> 01:25:25,164
What is this?

1299
01:25:25,414 --> 01:25:27,206
No one here
gives a straightforward response!

1300
01:25:27,414 --> 01:25:28,956
Didn't I tell you to think twice, sir?

1301
01:25:34,081 --> 01:25:34,956
Hey, Narayana!

1302
01:25:35,373 --> 01:25:37,914
Why have you come with so many cops?
Were you missing me?

1303
01:25:38,623 --> 01:25:41,414
With the kind of bail you have, you need
my permission before leaving the city.

1304
01:25:41,581 --> 01:25:44,123
But you roam as you please.
And why wouldn't I miss you?

1305
01:25:45,123 --> 01:25:46,331
We have to report to the station.
Let's go.

1306
01:25:46,539 --> 01:25:47,789
What will you do if I don't?

1307
01:25:48,248 --> 01:25:49,748
I'll grab your collar and drag you there!

1308
01:25:49,873 --> 01:25:51,206
You will do no such thing!

1309
01:25:51,289 --> 01:25:52,373
Run for your life!

1310
01:25:59,039 --> 01:26:00,164
Hey!

1311
01:26:01,289 --> 01:26:02,248
He hit him!

1312
01:26:02,581 --> 01:26:03,623
He is a cop.

1313
01:26:03,831 --> 01:26:04,998
Are you going to crush him?

1314
01:26:05,414 --> 01:26:07,456
Let go of him. Leave him. Idiots!

1315
01:26:08,706 --> 01:26:09,623
Mohammed.

1316
01:26:10,956 --> 01:26:11,831
Mohammed!

1317
01:26:11,956 --> 01:26:13,289
Sir, over here!

1318
01:26:13,664 --> 01:26:16,164
I have been telling you
to handle it with care!

1319
01:26:17,498 --> 01:26:18,873
- Hey, Samba.
- Yes?

1320
01:26:19,664 --> 01:26:20,664
What is the gentleman saying?

1321
01:26:20,748 --> 01:26:22,248
He says he will kill us if we let him go.

1322
01:26:22,331 --> 01:26:23,539
Bravo!

1323
01:26:25,331 --> 01:26:26,248
Narayana…

1324
01:26:27,831 --> 01:26:29,373
Venkata Swamy had called you, right?

1325
01:26:30,706 --> 01:26:31,914
He asked you to pick me up, right?

1326
01:26:33,289 --> 01:26:34,706
Go, tell the old man.

1327
01:26:35,581 --> 01:26:37,498
Ramana's collar is not starched.

1328
01:26:38,623 --> 01:26:40,748
It is stiff with arrogance.

1329
01:26:41,706 --> 01:26:43,456
Tell him if he touches it,
he will burn himself.

1330
01:26:47,664 --> 01:26:49,039
Gun? My gun!

1331
01:26:49,498 --> 01:26:51,331
What will you do with the CI's gun?

1332
01:26:51,873 --> 01:26:52,914
You want to play with it?

1333
01:26:53,414 --> 01:26:54,289
Give it back.

1334
01:26:55,206 --> 01:26:56,164
You…

1335
01:26:57,748 --> 01:26:58,623
Sir.

1336
01:27:03,748 --> 01:27:05,998
- Why did you take a picture?
- In case I need it…

1337
01:27:06,081 --> 01:27:07,081
To garland?

1338
01:27:09,289 --> 01:27:10,248
Hey!

1339
01:27:11,331 --> 01:27:12,623
Escort the CI to his Jeep.

1340
01:27:15,581 --> 01:27:16,456
Ramana!

1341
01:27:26,873 --> 01:27:27,748
What is the matter?

1342
01:27:28,748 --> 01:27:29,748
Why were the police here?

1343
01:27:29,873 --> 01:27:31,873
Your son went
to Minister Vasundhara's house.

1344
01:27:32,248 --> 01:27:33,373
He beat up their people.

1345
01:27:33,748 --> 01:27:35,331
He damaged their furniture.

1346
01:27:35,498 --> 01:27:36,914
We came to question him,
and he's threatening us!

1347
01:27:37,414 --> 01:27:38,706
I'm telling you,
I will not spare him!

1348
01:27:39,164 --> 01:27:40,039
It's a warning!

1349
01:27:40,539 --> 01:27:41,581
Hey, not right now!

1350
01:27:42,039 --> 01:27:44,039
Not right now.
We will take care of it later!

1351
01:27:44,123 --> 01:27:45,539
Hey, move! Give way!

1352
01:27:47,914 --> 01:27:49,206
Are you a rowdy?

1353
01:27:50,498 --> 01:27:51,914
- Or some goon?
- Wow!

1354
01:27:54,164 --> 01:27:56,164
Mr. Satyam has finally opened his mouth
and chided me.

1355
01:27:58,039 --> 01:27:59,081
It's going to rain today.

1356
01:27:59,373 --> 01:28:00,706
He only smashed things.

1357
01:28:01,039 --> 01:28:02,914
I would have burnt the place down.

1358
01:28:02,998 --> 01:28:05,289
You say enough things
to instigate him.

1359
01:28:06,539 --> 01:28:07,414
Hey!

1360
01:28:07,831 --> 01:28:09,706
If you have to sign, just go and sign.

1361
01:28:10,164 --> 01:28:11,331
Why did you have to fight?

1362
01:28:11,706 --> 01:28:14,623
They filed a case against me.
Do you expect me to honor them?

1363
01:28:15,581 --> 01:28:17,414
Should I sit gazing out of the window,
just like you?

1364
01:28:18,581 --> 01:28:20,748
To believe he's searching for his wife…
Hyderabad is not that way.

1365
01:28:21,123 --> 01:28:22,081
It's this way.

1366
01:28:22,373 --> 01:28:23,748
No one knows what he keeps looking at.

1367
01:28:25,414 --> 01:28:27,081
I did what was written in the complaint.

1368
01:28:27,248 --> 01:28:30,039
Has he killed anyone
that you're interrogating him?

1369
01:28:30,164 --> 01:28:31,206
Bujji!

1370
01:28:33,498 --> 01:28:34,373
Hey…

1371
01:28:35,331 --> 01:28:37,289
Do you even know why she left me?

1372
01:28:39,123 --> 01:28:40,164
For you.

1373
01:28:41,623 --> 01:28:42,998
After the blast at the warehouse…

1374
01:28:45,414 --> 01:28:47,956
I wanted to get your uncle out of jail.

1375
01:28:49,664 --> 01:28:52,414
And she wanted to take you to the hospital
for your eye.

1376
01:28:53,998 --> 01:28:55,373
We had a fight over our priorities.

1377
01:28:57,498 --> 01:28:59,248
I was young and arrogant.

1378
01:28:59,539 --> 01:29:00,539
I scolded your mother.

1379
01:29:00,998 --> 01:29:03,706
I mentioned that I knew
when to get my son treated.

1380
01:29:04,123 --> 01:29:05,081
Satyam!

1381
01:29:10,623 --> 01:29:12,039
When she wanted to take you and leave…

1382
01:29:12,956 --> 01:29:16,914
in my state of confusion,
I requested the door to be closed.

1383
01:29:17,748 --> 01:29:20,164
Your aunt never disobeys her brother.

1384
01:29:21,331 --> 01:29:22,581
She shut the door on your mother.

1385
01:29:31,539 --> 01:29:34,623
That broke your mother's heart
and she left.

1386
01:29:36,206 --> 01:29:37,498
Even at the court,

1387
01:29:38,206 --> 01:29:39,831
she asked your aunt about you.

1388
01:29:41,914 --> 01:29:45,289
Bujji… please tell me his eye is fine.

1389
01:29:47,664 --> 01:29:49,456
They say it won't go back to normal,
sister-in-law.

1390
01:29:50,539 --> 01:29:52,248
They said it should have been
treated immediately.

1391
01:29:55,289 --> 01:29:57,123
Enraged that you had lost your eye,

1392
01:29:57,498 --> 01:30:00,373
though your uncle was the one who
stabbed, she directed her finger at me.

1393
01:30:01,498 --> 01:30:03,164
Since his daughter had returned to him,

1394
01:30:03,623 --> 01:30:05,789
your grandfather didn't say
I was innocent.

1395
01:30:06,581 --> 01:30:09,123
Marx's elder brother was dead,
and his enemy was convicted.

1396
01:30:09,206 --> 01:30:10,664
So, Marx remained silent.

1397
01:30:10,748 --> 01:30:11,914
JUNIOR CIVIL JUDGE JUDICIAL MAGISTRATE
FIRST CLASS COURT GUNTUR

1398
01:30:12,539 --> 01:30:14,498
I was behind bars for ten years.

1399
01:30:14,998 --> 01:30:16,539
So, I couldn't come out.

1400
01:30:17,373 --> 01:30:19,664
During the ten years I spent in prison…

1401
01:30:20,789 --> 01:30:22,623
there was nobody here
to close the doors on her.

1402
01:30:24,081 --> 01:30:24,998
And yet, she didn't return.

1403
01:30:25,873 --> 01:30:27,206
Why didn't she take you back?

1404
01:30:28,206 --> 01:30:29,248
Isn't that what you should be asking?

1405
01:30:30,206 --> 01:30:31,581
Why do you get into a brawl instead?

1406
01:30:32,664 --> 01:30:34,623
I can't come up with a solution
to my problem.

1407
01:30:34,998 --> 01:30:37,873
That's why I keep staring
out of the window.

1408
01:30:39,289 --> 01:30:42,206
You, on the other hand,
don't even know what the problem is!

1409
01:30:42,831 --> 01:30:44,956
That's why, instead of talking,
you choose to take the stairs.

1410
01:30:46,373 --> 01:30:47,873
I'm afraid that in four years…

1411
01:30:48,414 --> 01:30:49,789
in just another four years…

1412
01:30:50,123 --> 01:30:52,081
you might sit next to me
in front of the window.

1413
01:30:56,498 --> 01:30:57,498
Ramana…

1414
01:30:58,998 --> 01:31:01,456
I know why my wife left me.

1415
01:31:02,539 --> 01:31:03,456
But…

1416
01:31:04,206 --> 01:31:06,331
Do you know
why your mother left you?

1417
01:31:15,373 --> 01:31:17,331
It's not that. Mr. Satyam…

1418
01:31:18,414 --> 01:31:19,789
Hello! Mr. Satyam!

1419
01:31:22,539 --> 01:31:23,914
She is the one who left me.
What should I do?

1420
01:31:26,331 --> 01:31:28,248
If I replace the broken furniture…

1421
01:31:29,206 --> 01:31:32,206
and ask her,
"Mom, why did you leave me? Tell me",

1422
01:31:32,456 --> 01:31:33,581
will she come back?

1423
01:31:34,456 --> 01:31:36,539
Is she going to wear a silk sari,
hold my hand, and come back?

1424
01:31:38,331 --> 01:31:39,456
Can you guarantee that?

1425
01:31:40,873 --> 01:31:42,373
There he goes with his songs.

1426
01:31:46,248 --> 01:31:47,831
She scolds and he laments.

1427
01:31:48,998 --> 01:31:50,248
They don't even give us
a chance to cry.

1428
01:31:51,581 --> 01:31:53,164
But both have dragged me to the curb.

1429
01:31:56,039 --> 01:31:58,081
I have found a great caption for my life.

1430
01:32:00,081 --> 01:32:01,331
"A father staring out of the window.

1431
01:32:02,873 --> 01:32:03,873
A mother shutting the door.

1432
01:32:04,664 --> 01:32:06,623
As for me…
A son out and about the streets."

1433
01:32:07,998 --> 01:32:09,623
Why are you holding a spoon?

1434
01:32:10,748 --> 01:32:12,414
Am I a jasmine to smell fragrant?

1435
01:32:12,873 --> 01:32:13,748
I am spicy chili!

1436
01:32:13,873 --> 01:32:15,873
That's why she didn't want me.
Why should I go and ask her again?

1437
01:32:17,581 --> 01:32:20,123
Every flirt seems to be getting lucky.

1438
01:32:20,748 --> 01:32:22,498
Not a single sad song is trending!

1439
01:32:22,664 --> 01:32:24,081
Yeah, you want others to cry for you.

1440
01:32:25,123 --> 01:32:25,998
Let's go for this one.

1441
01:32:26,081 --> 01:32:26,956
Have you found one finally?

1442
01:32:28,331 --> 01:32:29,831
A little on the side.

1443
01:32:30,164 --> 01:32:31,998
- Is this okay?
- Yes. Perfect.

1444
01:32:33,581 --> 01:32:35,206
Three, two, one!

1445
01:32:37,373 --> 01:32:44,289
Your love's eyes caress you
And yet why do you stay unmoved?

1446
01:32:44,998 --> 01:32:51,706
I cast a net and wait patiently
But is this all in vain?

1447
01:32:53,914 --> 01:32:56,664
She has made a reel on Insta.
I guess it's for you.

1448
01:33:03,789 --> 01:33:10,331
My darling friend, my heart throb
Look at me once, please

1449
01:33:15,539 --> 01:33:16,956
Must be for the video likes.

1450
01:33:18,414 --> 01:33:19,498
Not because she likes me.

1451
01:33:21,623 --> 01:33:25,664
Sister, your earrings are nice.
Are they available on Amazon?

1452
01:33:26,289 --> 01:33:27,456
Come and take them when I die.

1453
01:33:27,914 --> 01:33:28,998
Why don't you tell the poor thing?

1454
01:33:30,581 --> 01:33:32,498
Someone who ignores a beautiful girl
like you has to be a fool.

1455
01:33:32,789 --> 01:33:33,748
You can always count on me.

1456
01:33:34,081 --> 01:33:34,956
Chill.

1457
01:33:35,456 --> 01:33:36,873
He seems to have a lot of free time.

1458
01:33:38,456 --> 01:33:41,039
Visit Shirdi once, dear.
Everything will fall into place.

1459
01:33:48,914 --> 01:33:51,206
When the CI went to meet him yesterday,
he snatched his gun and threatened him.

1460
01:33:51,956 --> 01:33:54,331
Clashes with the cops
and meetings with Madhu.

1461
01:33:54,623 --> 01:33:56,581
He is purposely creating a nuisance
out of sheer vengeance.

1462
01:33:56,664 --> 01:33:58,664
I don't want to talk about the past.

1463
01:33:59,414 --> 01:34:01,206
What did your son take
in exchange for that photo?

1464
01:34:01,289 --> 01:34:03,539
Whatever he had taken from you
for signing the papers.

1465
01:34:05,498 --> 01:34:06,706
I will make a call one more time.

1466
01:34:08,081 --> 01:34:09,664
Ask him to keep quiet,
at least until the elections conclude.

1467
01:34:28,206 --> 01:34:30,081
Why have they brought
Mr. Satyam's gramophone here?

1468
01:34:33,873 --> 01:34:34,914
Play the rhythm.
Let me show you.

1469
01:35:02,748 --> 01:35:06,206
Bro, it doesn't matter how big the bill is

1470
01:35:06,498 --> 01:35:09,956
I'm feeling low and I will have a full

1471
01:35:10,331 --> 01:35:13,623
A thorn pierced through my heart

1472
01:35:13,998 --> 01:35:17,331
My pain has worsened

1473
01:35:17,623 --> 01:35:21,164
The world has changed
The evil has united

1474
01:35:21,414 --> 01:35:24,873
For a sensitive man like me
Every day is a rotting hell

1475
01:35:24,956 --> 01:35:28,706
No one to blame
I'm angry with myself

1476
01:35:28,956 --> 01:35:32,914
When the sky remains unreachable
How long can we leap?

1477
01:35:34,206 --> 01:35:37,831
Hey, people think they have people
But no one actually belongs

1478
01:35:37,914 --> 01:35:41,414
All relations, and endearments
Are just part of lip service

1479
01:35:41,664 --> 01:35:45,206
Hey, vexed eyes are dry of tears

1480
01:35:45,414 --> 01:35:49,414
I look around and find that
I am my only lover

1481
01:36:26,081 --> 01:36:27,123
Brother!

1482
01:36:27,373 --> 01:36:29,414
Spicy and pungent!

1483
01:36:31,081 --> 01:36:33,164
Stinging chili powder!

1484
01:36:40,623 --> 01:36:43,956
Sir!
A contract has been issued to kill you.

1485
01:36:44,081 --> 01:36:45,331
Ammu sent me here.

1486
01:36:45,789 --> 01:36:50,498
Iron bar, heavy hammer
A single blow and broken by sparks!

1487
01:36:52,664 --> 01:36:53,539
Hey!

1488
01:36:55,373 --> 01:36:56,539
Is there a Ramana here?

1489
01:36:59,456 --> 01:37:00,456
One second.

1490
01:37:00,831 --> 01:37:01,748
Hello…

1491
01:37:02,789 --> 01:37:04,289
I see you are with a red light.

1492
01:37:04,914 --> 01:37:06,081
Are you taking us to the area?

1493
01:37:13,581 --> 01:37:14,539
Got you!

1494
01:37:40,331 --> 01:37:41,664
Hey, come here.
Get down.

1495
01:37:46,831 --> 01:37:50,164
Brother, when we asked for Ramana,
two of them had come forward.

1496
01:37:50,498 --> 01:37:51,831
We brought them both as a precaution.

1497
01:37:52,081 --> 01:37:53,164
Hey, Amazon!

1498
01:37:53,623 --> 01:37:55,498
Stop the chatter and open the parcel.

1499
01:37:59,081 --> 01:38:00,081
Hey, get down!

1500
01:38:00,706 --> 01:38:01,873
Hey, bloody get up!

1501
01:38:05,664 --> 01:38:06,623
Sir!

1502
01:38:07,331 --> 01:38:08,206
Get up!

1503
01:38:08,289 --> 01:38:09,873
Sir! Please get up!

1504
01:38:35,331 --> 01:38:36,248
Sir…

1505
01:38:37,164 --> 01:38:38,331
- Sir…
- Hey, Samba!

1506
01:38:39,456 --> 01:38:40,581
I don't think Samba is around, sir.

1507
01:38:40,706 --> 01:38:42,914
- Samba!
- Sir! Balu, sir.

1508
01:38:43,956 --> 01:38:45,164
Sir, it's Balu.

1509
01:38:47,873 --> 01:38:48,998
What are you doing here?

1510
01:38:49,956 --> 01:38:51,039
Ammu has sent me, sir.

1511
01:38:51,206 --> 01:38:52,581
- Ammu?
- Yes.

1512
01:38:53,914 --> 01:38:54,914
Why did she send you?

1513
01:38:54,998 --> 01:38:57,206
Some Babji has been given a contract
to kill you, sir.

1514
01:38:57,289 --> 01:38:58,998
I tried to inform you, but I was
punched and knocked unconscious.

1515
01:38:59,831 --> 01:39:00,706
By who?

1516
01:39:12,831 --> 01:39:14,081
Who are all these people?

1517
01:39:15,206 --> 01:39:17,623
Are we appointing new drivers
for our trucks?

1518
01:39:18,123 --> 01:39:19,206
They are the contract holders, sir.

1519
01:39:19,414 --> 01:39:20,414
- Contract?
- Yes.

1520
01:39:20,623 --> 01:39:21,498
For what?

1521
01:39:21,914 --> 01:39:23,789
Ammu has sent me
to tell you exactly that, sir.

1522
01:39:23,873 --> 01:39:24,748
Hey!

1523
01:39:24,831 --> 01:39:27,206
We are not on talking terms.
Why would she send you?

1524
01:39:27,373 --> 01:39:29,373
Spare me your personal issues, sir!

1525
01:39:29,456 --> 01:39:31,623
Babji has been paid to kill you.

1526
01:39:31,748 --> 01:39:33,331
I wanted to tell you the same,
but I was struck and silenced!

1527
01:39:34,539 --> 01:39:35,414
By who?

1528
01:39:37,081 --> 01:39:38,456
It was you, sir!

1529
01:39:43,414 --> 01:39:44,289
For what?

1530
01:39:45,164 --> 01:39:48,664
Gosh! I curse my fate!

1531
01:39:48,748 --> 01:39:49,664
Hey!

1532
01:39:50,998 --> 01:39:52,498
He has swallowed a mic.

1533
01:39:52,748 --> 01:39:53,873
Bloody idiot.

1534
01:39:58,873 --> 01:39:59,831
Hey…

1535
01:40:00,373 --> 01:40:01,498
do you want to snip?

1536
01:40:02,206 --> 01:40:04,706
I don't want his hair.
I want his head! Get it!

1537
01:41:20,414 --> 01:41:21,331
What happened?

1538
01:41:21,789 --> 01:41:22,664
He is sleeping.

1539
01:41:23,081 --> 01:41:24,373
Turn off the lights and turn on the AC.

1540
01:41:24,456 --> 01:41:26,039
Wake him up, you fool!

1541
01:41:26,873 --> 01:41:27,873
Hey, get up!

1542
01:41:28,373 --> 01:41:34,248
Wake up, wake up!
Oh, my king!

1543
01:41:47,164 --> 01:41:48,831
Who took the contract to kill me?

1544
01:41:48,914 --> 01:41:50,248
Hey, half-bottle!

1545
01:41:51,248 --> 01:41:53,581
I'm the contract killer
tasked with ending your life.

1546
01:41:53,914 --> 01:41:55,248
I am Babji.

1547
01:41:56,498 --> 01:41:57,831
Gelatin Babji.

1548
01:41:58,998 --> 01:42:00,539
You are very costly.

1549
01:42:01,956 --> 01:42:03,206
I took one crore rupees.

1550
01:42:04,664 --> 01:42:05,748
Remember this before you die.

1551
01:42:06,248 --> 01:42:07,748
Why would Ammu give you one crore rupees?

1552
01:42:09,664 --> 01:42:10,623
Hey!

1553
01:42:11,623 --> 01:42:13,248
Is there a queue system now?

1554
01:42:13,831 --> 01:42:14,789
Move!

1555
01:42:59,081 --> 01:43:00,498
How audacious of you
to put a price tag on me!

1556
01:43:02,289 --> 01:43:03,289
My name is Ramana.

1557
01:43:04,123 --> 01:43:05,373
I'm not for sale.

1558
01:43:05,831 --> 01:43:06,831
- Hey, Balu.
- Sir?

1559
01:43:07,414 --> 01:43:08,331
Who are all these men?

1560
01:43:08,498 --> 01:43:09,748
Why did Ammu send them?

1561
01:43:10,081 --> 01:43:12,414
Why would Ammu send them, sir?
Do you think she is crazy?

1562
01:43:12,498 --> 01:43:13,623
Ammu has sent me!

1563
01:43:14,206 --> 01:43:17,373
You're the one bothering me
by constantly chanting Ammu's name, sir!

1564
01:43:18,039 --> 01:43:19,206
It was Babji who took the contract.

1565
01:43:19,873 --> 01:43:22,456
It's Vyra Venkata Swamy who
wants you dead! Your grandfather!

1566
01:43:24,789 --> 01:43:26,998
- Who?
- Your bloody old grandfather.

1567
01:43:27,414 --> 01:43:28,664
- My grandfather?
- Yes.

1568
01:43:28,956 --> 01:43:30,581
Hey, what is this meeting about?

1569
01:43:30,664 --> 01:43:31,539
Keep quiet!

1570
01:43:33,373 --> 01:43:34,873
Why does the old man want to kill me?

1571
01:43:35,039 --> 01:43:35,914
Oh, God!

1572
01:43:36,289 --> 01:43:38,373
Hey! I'm a saint with no enemies.

1573
01:43:39,248 --> 01:43:40,373
A saint?

1574
01:43:41,581 --> 01:43:43,789
Sir! Do you even know its meaning?

1575
01:43:44,039 --> 01:43:45,956
Great souls like Dharmaraju and Vidura--

1576
01:43:46,039 --> 01:43:47,539
- Hey, discourse!
- Wait, man!

1577
01:43:50,039 --> 01:43:51,539
"I will create destruction
each time we meet."

1578
01:43:51,873 --> 01:43:53,539
"I give autographs only to my fans."
When you say so, why won't they kill you?

1579
01:43:53,748 --> 01:43:54,748
You think they will pamper you?

1580
01:43:58,456 --> 01:43:59,498
Hey!

1581
01:43:59,831 --> 01:44:00,914
Hey!

1582
01:44:09,414 --> 01:44:10,498
Hey!

1583
01:44:10,998 --> 01:44:12,039
Are you gone?

1584
01:44:29,789 --> 01:44:31,664
- How many fingers are these?
- Whose fingers?

1585
01:44:34,123 --> 01:44:35,206
Mine's only one.

1586
01:44:36,498 --> 01:44:37,873
I guess he has lost both.

1587
01:44:38,289 --> 01:44:39,998
- Is he blind?
- You doubt it?

1588
01:44:40,081 --> 01:44:41,331
Blind? Who is blind?

1589
01:44:41,414 --> 01:44:43,164
- Who is that?
- You… Bloody…

1590
01:44:44,081 --> 01:44:46,539
You said your name was some Tin or Can.
What was it?

1591
01:44:47,831 --> 01:44:48,998
Gelatin Babji, brother.

1592
01:44:49,373 --> 01:44:50,248
Christian?

1593
01:44:50,664 --> 01:44:52,248
No, brother. Hindu.

1594
01:44:52,581 --> 01:44:53,539
What is Gelatin?

1595
01:44:54,248 --> 01:44:55,831
That's my profession, brother.

1596
01:44:56,206 --> 01:44:58,498
I use gelatin sticks
and blast rocks in quarries.

1597
01:44:58,789 --> 01:45:00,581
Are the sticks this long?

1598
01:45:00,873 --> 01:45:01,789
No.

1599
01:45:02,039 --> 01:45:03,039
They are only this long.

1600
01:45:07,873 --> 01:45:08,831
Hey!

1601
01:45:09,123 --> 01:45:10,373
Where is my grandpa right now?

1602
01:45:10,998 --> 01:45:13,373
How would I know
where your grandfather is, brother?

1603
01:45:15,081 --> 01:45:16,873
Tell me.
Where is the old man?

1604
01:45:17,789 --> 01:45:19,039
- Surya!
- Brother!

1605
01:45:19,414 --> 01:45:20,998
Share the location with brother.

1606
01:45:38,831 --> 01:45:40,664
What's up, Venkata Swamy?
Is the scenery so good?

1607
01:45:40,748 --> 01:45:41,831
You seem engrossed!

1608
01:45:42,373 --> 01:45:43,539
Why are you here?

1609
01:45:44,164 --> 01:45:45,498
What do you want from me?

1610
01:45:45,914 --> 01:45:48,664
I'm done with you,
why did you still send goons at me?

1611
01:45:48,789 --> 01:45:49,914
I sent goons?!

1612
01:45:50,539 --> 01:45:52,539
Hey, what is
he talking about, Narayana?

1613
01:45:53,914 --> 01:45:54,956
Mr. Narayana!

1614
01:45:55,623 --> 01:45:57,956
Sir! Mr. Narayana! Sorry, sir.
The job is not done.

1615
01:45:59,248 --> 01:46:00,539
Uncle, was it you who sent them?

1616
01:46:01,581 --> 01:46:03,664
Who told you to send Babji to him?

1617
01:46:03,748 --> 01:46:05,706
Didn't you tell me
he shouldn't open his mouth?

1618
01:46:05,956 --> 01:46:06,914
What if I did?

1619
01:46:08,039 --> 01:46:10,956
People like him will only be quiet
when they die. There is no other option.

1620
01:46:12,039 --> 01:46:13,498
- Hey, Babji!
- Brother?

1621
01:46:13,581 --> 01:46:15,831
Pass the phone. Let's play them
the sound of Ramana's voice.

1622
01:46:16,039 --> 01:46:16,956
Here, brother.

1623
01:46:17,039 --> 01:46:18,498
- Hey, this side.
- It's okay, brother.

1624
01:46:18,581 --> 01:46:19,539
Hey!

1625
01:46:20,414 --> 01:46:21,539
Who are you calling?

1626
01:46:21,998 --> 01:46:22,873
Hey, close them.

1627
01:46:38,789 --> 01:46:41,748
Before coming here, we loaded the cars
and set the trigger on the phone.

1628
01:46:41,831 --> 01:46:44,164
The explosion and cars soaring
amidst the dust were an added bonus.

1629
01:46:44,289 --> 01:46:48,456
Madhu and you want to trample on
my daughter's and my political careers?

1630
01:46:48,581 --> 01:46:50,623
Why will I join hands
with that pickpocket?

1631
01:46:51,248 --> 01:46:53,081
He came to me and I thrashed him.

1632
01:46:53,623 --> 01:46:55,039
He snatched my wallet in the flow.

1633
01:46:56,706 --> 01:46:58,289
You owe me the five thousand rupees
that I lost.

1634
01:46:59,248 --> 01:47:00,248
Look, Venkata Swamy!

1635
01:47:00,331 --> 01:47:02,498
The next time I come, cars won't fly.

1636
01:47:02,831 --> 01:47:04,164
You will fly along with your building!

1637
01:47:06,039 --> 01:47:07,789
- Hey, come on.
- Take me along, brother.

1638
01:47:08,164 --> 01:47:10,706
Why do you water those?
Water the dried-up plants.

1639
01:47:19,539 --> 01:47:20,581
He is not home.

1640
01:47:20,914 --> 01:47:21,873
Is that the girl?

1641
01:47:21,956 --> 01:47:22,831
That's the mother.

1642
01:47:22,914 --> 01:47:24,039
Come in and sit.

1643
01:47:27,081 --> 01:47:28,664
- Is she the one?
- Her younger sister.

1644
01:47:28,789 --> 01:47:30,331
Someone loves tea.

1645
01:47:30,956 --> 01:47:32,748
Ask them if they want some, Balu.

1646
01:47:32,914 --> 01:47:34,914
- Is that the mother?
- It's the father with a sore throat!

1647
01:47:35,748 --> 01:47:37,248
- Give it.
- Sir.

1648
01:47:44,456 --> 01:47:46,123
Do you think we should say thanks?

1649
01:47:46,289 --> 01:47:48,706
- Someone seems to be expecting it.
- Drat!

1650
01:47:48,789 --> 01:47:51,248
When I heard you were safe,
I wore a sari to go to the temple.

1651
01:47:51,539 --> 01:47:53,373
If I weren't safe,
would you be wearing pants?

1652
01:47:58,081 --> 01:47:59,914
When will you understand my heart, sir?

1653
01:48:00,081 --> 01:48:02,581
You play cricket and
kabaddi with my heart…

1654
01:48:02,998 --> 01:48:04,373
but I'm supposed to understand!

1655
01:48:05,873 --> 01:48:07,456
Why am I being tortured, Balu?

1656
01:48:07,539 --> 01:48:08,539
No idea, baby.

1657
01:48:08,664 --> 01:48:09,873
Why do you want to involve him?

1658
01:48:10,706 --> 01:48:11,706
Idiot!

1659
01:48:11,998 --> 01:48:14,123
- What did I do, sir?
- You did nothing.

1660
01:48:14,706 --> 01:48:15,789
You are a serpent.

1661
01:48:16,789 --> 01:48:18,956
Did you ever let us sit
next to each other?

1662
01:48:19,289 --> 01:48:20,831
You would pull her away
calling her "baby" all the time.

1663
01:48:21,164 --> 01:48:22,039
Idiot!

1664
01:48:24,123 --> 01:48:26,206
Is sitting next to you enough
or shall I sit in your lap?

1665
01:48:31,956 --> 01:48:33,664
I took her to school with these hands.

1666
01:48:33,748 --> 01:48:34,748
What happened, Balu?

1667
01:48:34,956 --> 01:48:37,164
She apologizes to him,
and he expresses his gratitude.

1668
01:48:37,248 --> 01:48:39,373
But is the girl fair or very fair?

1669
01:48:40,373 --> 01:48:41,998
She is green.
What do you care?

1670
01:48:47,123 --> 01:48:48,206
Hey!

1671
01:48:49,789 --> 01:48:51,039
Why did you go to him?

1672
01:48:51,498 --> 01:48:53,789
She asked me to warn Ramana
about Gelatin Babji.

1673
01:48:54,164 --> 01:48:55,623
- This one?
- Who else? This one?

1674
01:48:57,039 --> 01:48:57,914
Hey!

1675
01:48:59,456 --> 01:49:02,039
I had asked you to get his signature.
Instead, you have been spying on me!

1676
01:49:04,456 --> 01:49:06,039
What makes you so captivated by him?

1677
01:49:07,373 --> 01:49:09,123
His own mother rejected him
and abandoned him.

1678
01:49:13,039 --> 01:49:14,331
I'm sure she didn't take a proper look.

1679
01:49:14,581 --> 01:49:16,373
And I believe
he didn't step into the house?

1680
01:49:17,081 --> 01:49:18,164
I stepped out myself.

1681
01:49:19,664 --> 01:49:21,956
He was ready to pick a fight.
Your mom told me.

1682
01:49:22,164 --> 01:49:23,456
That's his way of showing love.

1683
01:49:24,581 --> 01:49:26,164
You don't seem to understand my situation.

1684
01:49:26,414 --> 01:49:28,664
Continue this and I will hang myself.
Be warned!

1685
01:49:30,914 --> 01:49:31,914
Balu…

1686
01:49:34,039 --> 01:49:35,039
What is this?

1687
01:49:35,414 --> 01:49:37,664
Are you threatening me that
you'll kill yourself? Go ahead!

1688
01:49:37,956 --> 01:49:39,331
That is meant for you.

1689
01:49:40,748 --> 01:49:44,498
If you can't kick the stool, there are
four of us here. One of us will do it.

1690
01:49:47,248 --> 01:49:48,248
Hey, silly girl!

1691
01:49:48,331 --> 01:49:51,456
Most Honorable Venkata Swamy
takes care of our needs.

1692
01:49:53,206 --> 01:49:55,956
But I like Honorable Venkata Ramana.

1693
01:50:05,331 --> 01:50:07,998
He visits Hyderabad frequently.
I wonder what's so interesting!

1694
01:50:08,248 --> 01:50:10,164
His mother probably
comes into his dreams every day.

1695
01:50:10,414 --> 01:50:12,414
The father and son
appear deeply engrossed.

1696
01:50:13,081 --> 01:50:14,539
Hey, get me the cloth!

1697
01:50:15,289 --> 01:50:17,664
Just the other day, they filed a case
and forced him to sign.

1698
01:50:17,873 --> 01:50:18,914
Moreover,

1699
01:50:19,248 --> 01:50:20,956
unsatisfied, they sent thugs after him.

1700
01:50:21,331 --> 01:50:24,414
Your dad wants you to find out
why a woman like her left you.

1701
01:50:24,498 --> 01:50:25,748
Go and ask her!

1702
01:50:26,206 --> 01:50:27,873
You don't pay attention
to the people around you.

1703
01:50:27,956 --> 01:50:28,998
Hey!

1704
01:50:31,873 --> 01:50:33,581
You have been badgering me for hours!

1705
01:50:33,998 --> 01:50:35,998
You closed the door on my mother,
and she left.

1706
01:50:37,289 --> 01:50:38,206
It's all your fault.

1707
01:50:38,456 --> 01:50:41,123
You are afraid
I would keep this in mind.

1708
01:50:42,248 --> 01:50:43,289
Who told you?

1709
01:50:43,789 --> 01:50:44,831
Did you have a dream?

1710
01:50:45,164 --> 01:50:47,748
Going somewhere implies leaving
and returning, not staying there.

1711
01:50:48,414 --> 01:50:49,956
I used to think drinking was an addiction.

1712
01:50:50,289 --> 01:50:51,498
But a mother is also an addiction.

1713
01:50:51,789 --> 01:50:52,789
I feel that now.

1714
01:50:52,873 --> 01:50:54,289
Don't take her name here anymore.

1715
01:50:55,331 --> 01:50:57,164
Hey, your dad will hear.

1716
01:50:57,331 --> 01:50:58,248
Let him!

1717
01:50:58,414 --> 01:50:59,748
I have heard why she left.

1718
01:51:00,081 --> 01:51:02,498
I have decided I don't want her.
Let him hear it!

1719
01:51:09,539 --> 01:51:11,873
All of us support Venkata Ramana.

1720
01:51:35,706 --> 01:51:36,706
Madam!

1721
01:51:37,456 --> 01:51:38,456
Madam!

1722
01:52:30,456 --> 01:52:34,498
Law Minister, Madam Vyra Vasundhara
met with an accident today.

1723
01:52:34,581 --> 01:52:37,831
A truck rammed into her convoy
on the way to the Secretariat,

1724
01:52:37,914 --> 01:52:39,373
severely injuring her.

1725
01:52:39,539 --> 01:52:42,623
She was immediately rushed
to Axis Hospital close by.

1726
01:52:42,706 --> 01:52:45,831
Doctors have confirmed injuries
to her head and arms.

1727
01:53:02,873 --> 01:53:06,123
Minister Vyra Vasundhara's appearing
before the media in a short while!

1728
01:53:06,248 --> 01:53:09,206
There's a press meet
in the conference hall

1729
01:53:09,331 --> 01:53:10,623
on the first floor of Axis Hospital!

1730
01:53:10,706 --> 01:53:14,664
She is expected to give her health updates
and the reasons for the accident.

1731
01:53:15,289 --> 01:53:16,623
We have learned that

1732
01:53:16,706 --> 01:53:20,414
Minister Vyra Vasundhara
has been under treatment for two days.

1733
01:53:23,039 --> 01:53:24,081
I am fine now.

1734
01:53:24,956 --> 01:53:26,789
I walked by myself here.

1735
01:53:27,539 --> 01:53:29,789
It took some time, but I came on my own.

1736
01:53:30,373 --> 01:53:31,414
Is your hand fractured?

1737
01:53:32,164 --> 01:53:33,498
Just a shoulder injury.

1738
01:53:36,664 --> 01:53:39,831
Kata Madhu has criticized
that you have abandoned your elder son.

1739
01:53:39,914 --> 01:53:41,289
- This is…
- Your response to this…

1740
01:53:41,498 --> 01:53:43,914
a press meet about her health updates.

1741
01:53:44,831 --> 01:53:46,998
Please don't divert the topic. Next.

1742
01:53:50,873 --> 01:53:53,456
This accident happened soon
after Kata Madhu's press meet.

1743
01:53:53,539 --> 01:53:55,289
So, is this an attempt to murder?

1744
01:53:56,373 --> 01:54:00,789
Ma'am, would you fight with rivals
like Hari Das and Madhu or let go?

1745
01:54:22,081 --> 01:54:24,706
I may let go of what I love.

1746
01:54:27,248 --> 01:54:28,873
I don't spare anything
that poses a threat to me.

1747
01:54:30,706 --> 01:54:33,914
In Kashi, the way we let go
of our favorite things for Ganga…

1748
01:54:35,581 --> 01:54:37,998
I have also let go
of some of my favorite ones.

1749
01:54:46,373 --> 01:54:48,331
We must somehow get Ramana back, Dad.

1750
01:54:50,081 --> 01:54:51,248
You got to help me.

1751
01:54:51,789 --> 01:54:52,706
Let go.

1752
01:54:54,539 --> 01:54:56,414
I don't insist out of adamance, Dad.

1753
01:54:56,789 --> 01:54:59,039
I didn't ask you
to let go of your adamance.

1754
01:55:00,206 --> 01:55:01,789
I meant, let go of your son.

1755
01:55:04,206 --> 01:55:05,289
You find it painful?

1756
01:55:06,498 --> 01:55:07,748
Well, you have raised him for ten years.

1757
01:55:09,331 --> 01:55:11,748
What about my pain
when I was asked to give up my daughter?

1758
01:55:12,581 --> 01:55:14,039
I had raised you for 25 years.

1759
01:55:15,706 --> 01:55:17,664
Your parenting for ten years is love.

1760
01:55:18,456 --> 01:55:21,206
But my parenting for 25 years
is selfishness?

1761
01:55:23,039 --> 01:55:26,164
If I am selfish,
then you are somewhat less selfish.

1762
01:55:27,164 --> 01:55:30,039
If yours is love,
then mine is bigger love.

1763
01:55:31,748 --> 01:55:34,081
If you still insist on going,
I won't stop you.

1764
01:55:36,206 --> 01:55:39,873
But this time when the warehouse
catches fire, your husband will be gone.

1765
01:55:40,373 --> 01:55:41,748
This time, it won't just
be an eye like before.

1766
01:55:42,664 --> 01:55:43,789
Your son himself will be gone.

1767
01:55:44,539 --> 01:55:46,373
- Dad?
- Yes, it's Dad.

1768
01:55:48,498 --> 01:55:49,498
Your dad.

1769
01:55:51,373 --> 01:55:53,498
The matchstick that ignited
the Guntur warehouse,

1770
01:55:53,998 --> 01:55:56,831
the broken petrol bottles,
the expense of five lakh rupees,

1771
01:55:57,081 --> 01:56:00,414
Marx's pockets that held it,
and dead Lenin's blood.

1772
01:56:00,498 --> 01:56:01,456
Everything!

1773
01:56:01,539 --> 01:56:04,581
Your dad was the person behind it all.

1774
01:56:15,248 --> 01:56:17,498
Mothers may not always be right.

1775
01:56:18,914 --> 01:56:21,039
But they never go wrong
in fulfilling their responsibilities.

1776
01:56:24,164 --> 01:56:25,789
Madam, one minute.
Mr. Kata Madhu accuses you

1777
01:56:25,873 --> 01:56:28,289
- of leaving your elder son like an orphan.
- Enough.

1778
01:56:28,373 --> 01:56:29,539
What's your take on this?

1779
01:56:32,789 --> 01:56:33,831
I am a mother.

1780
01:56:34,789 --> 01:56:37,414
Never ask a mother
what she has done for her children.

1781
01:56:40,289 --> 01:56:41,664
You won't know even if I tell you.

1782
01:56:42,706 --> 01:56:44,081
You won't understand
even if you find out.

1783
01:57:02,998 --> 01:57:06,331
The media and we are aware that Hari Das
was responsible for this accident.

1784
01:57:06,414 --> 01:57:07,664
Only you don't know.

1785
01:57:09,289 --> 01:57:11,039
But no one has the guts to speak up.

1786
01:57:12,123 --> 01:57:15,164
The driver would claim he had not slept
and couldn't apply the brakes.

1787
01:57:15,248 --> 01:57:16,539
And he would be out in six months.

1788
01:57:17,081 --> 01:57:18,373
That is Hari Das.

1789
01:57:19,456 --> 01:57:23,998
People like you ignore rogues like him
but come and challenge old men like me.

1790
01:57:25,289 --> 01:57:26,623
Tell him if you have the guts.

1791
01:57:28,373 --> 01:57:29,914
"I am Vasundhara's son.

1792
01:57:30,831 --> 01:57:32,081
Face me if you can.

1793
01:57:32,706 --> 01:57:34,289
I am called Guntur Chili."

1794
01:57:35,664 --> 01:57:37,373
Don't come up with excuses like
not knowing the address.

1795
01:57:38,206 --> 01:57:40,873
Everyone pays a visit after an accident.

1796
01:57:42,039 --> 01:57:43,581
Go see him.

1797
01:57:44,873 --> 01:57:47,456
Then come, twirl your mustache,
and tell your mom, "I am your son."

1798
01:57:48,081 --> 01:57:49,914
If you can't,
then weep and keep quiet.

1799
01:57:51,664 --> 01:57:53,706
Why do you always meddle with him,

1800
01:57:53,831 --> 01:57:56,873
make it a big issue,
and turn it into a calamity?

1801
01:57:57,706 --> 01:58:00,039
I mean,
you are so wise in political affairs!

1802
01:58:00,331 --> 01:58:03,289
When it comes to family,
why do you get so emotional and--

1803
01:58:03,373 --> 01:58:04,831
- Pani!
- Sir.

1804
01:58:04,956 --> 01:58:05,998
Let me tell you a story.

1805
01:58:06,123 --> 01:58:07,956
- Listen with some patience.
- Sir.

1806
01:58:09,289 --> 01:58:12,331
A man built himself a solid fort
only by playing caste politics.

1807
01:58:12,914 --> 01:58:14,664
He won thrice consecutively.

1808
01:58:15,289 --> 01:58:18,456
His daughter got into
an inter-caste marriage and left him.

1809
01:58:18,748 --> 01:58:21,581
People said, "You couldn't make your
daughter marry into your own caste.

1810
01:58:21,914 --> 01:58:24,039
What can you possibly do for the others?"

1811
01:58:24,456 --> 01:58:25,914
- And he lost.
- Addepalli Niranjan

1812
01:58:25,998 --> 01:58:30,248
has won against the sitting MLA
Vyra Venkata Swamy with 5433 votes.

1813
01:58:30,331 --> 01:58:33,581
To win the election again,
his daughter would have to come back.

1814
01:58:33,748 --> 01:58:34,998
He finally brought her back.

1815
01:58:36,789 --> 01:58:38,206
There was a lot involved, of course.

1816
01:58:45,873 --> 01:58:47,039
- Narayana…
- Uncle!

1817
01:58:47,414 --> 01:58:49,914
Uncle! He stands a chance
if we take him to Vijayawada.

1818
01:58:50,289 --> 01:58:53,248
What if he gets stuck in traffic
before reaching the hospital?

1819
01:58:53,498 --> 01:58:54,623
- Uncle!
- Narayana!

1820
01:58:55,164 --> 01:58:57,081
- Let him die.
- Narayana…

1821
01:59:03,498 --> 01:59:05,414
He got his daughter married
to his nephew.

1822
01:59:05,664 --> 01:59:07,081
He made her contest elections.

1823
01:59:07,289 --> 01:59:09,248
Since she married into the same caste,
they elected her.

1824
01:59:09,373 --> 01:59:10,498
She even became a minister.

1825
01:59:11,206 --> 01:59:17,539
Now, he desires his grandson,
born into his own caste, to become an MP.

1826
01:59:17,706 --> 01:59:21,039
Exactly at that moment, here's what
appears on his daughter's phone.

1827
01:59:21,414 --> 01:59:22,331
Here…

1828
01:59:28,456 --> 01:59:31,331
Twenty-five years of control.
Isn't it slipping out of hand?

1829
01:59:33,206 --> 01:59:34,581
Where is emotion involved in all this?

1830
01:59:34,873 --> 01:59:36,498
It's all politics, right?

1831
01:59:56,831 --> 01:59:58,414
I haven't seen you before.

1832
02:00:00,164 --> 02:00:01,331
I never came here.

1833
02:00:02,873 --> 02:00:04,164
What brings you here now?

1834
02:00:06,914 --> 02:00:07,998
To eat some fritters.

1835
02:00:08,123 --> 02:00:09,914
Don't you get them in your place?

1836
02:00:11,789 --> 02:00:13,623
Each location
has its distinctive specialty.

1837
02:00:14,373 --> 02:00:15,498
What's special here?

1838
02:00:20,206 --> 02:00:21,123
Hari Das.

1839
02:00:23,956 --> 02:00:26,081
What is so special about him?

1840
02:00:27,164 --> 02:00:28,623
He wants to kill my mother.

1841
02:00:29,039 --> 02:00:30,248
Who is your mother?

1842
02:00:31,748 --> 02:00:32,789
Vyra Vasundhara.

1843
02:00:35,914 --> 02:00:36,914
My grandfather told me…

1844
02:00:38,748 --> 02:00:40,873
to sit at home and cry
when Das kills my mother.

1845
02:00:43,581 --> 02:00:44,581
Tell me, Uncle.

1846
02:00:45,748 --> 02:00:47,289
How disgusting it would be if I cried!

1847
02:00:49,039 --> 02:00:51,539
As disgusting as a wig
on your bald head!

1848
02:00:53,539 --> 02:00:54,456
That's why…

1849
02:00:55,206 --> 02:00:56,498
I have come to kill him.

1850
02:00:59,789 --> 02:01:01,623
- Are you carrying a knife?
- Yes.

1851
02:01:02,539 --> 02:01:03,998
Where are you hiding it?

1852
02:01:04,164 --> 02:01:05,414
Six feet one inch.

1853
02:01:06,248 --> 02:01:07,331
It's not possible to hide it.

1854
02:01:28,956 --> 02:01:31,206
Brother, there's a guy claiming
that he has come to kill you.

1855
02:01:34,831 --> 02:01:37,956
I've been here for the last forty years.
I'll show you who Das is. Come on.

1856
02:01:40,956 --> 02:01:45,039
They say after the Stuvartupuram Colony
was gone, they had all joined his gang.

1857
02:01:45,706 --> 02:01:47,873
Knives, bombs, you name it!

1858
02:01:48,331 --> 02:01:52,206
Everything needed for survival
and killing is available for sale here.

1859
02:01:52,664 --> 02:01:53,623
These youngsters?

1860
02:01:53,706 --> 02:01:56,456
Only they can act on impulse
without thinking of consequences.

1861
02:01:56,873 --> 02:01:59,206
That's why Hari Das only uses them.

1862
02:02:03,998 --> 02:02:06,206
Is this Hari Das?

1863
02:02:09,706 --> 02:02:10,789
That's quite a big head.

1864
02:02:11,289 --> 02:02:12,164
But I will pluck it and go.

1865
02:02:43,623 --> 02:02:44,873
What is this, Uncle?

1866
02:02:45,748 --> 02:02:47,123
Are they ladies or rowdies?

1867
02:02:51,414 --> 02:02:53,248
Even the sweepers are
delivering flying kicks!

1868
02:02:53,456 --> 02:02:55,331
You want Das's head, right?

1869
02:02:57,414 --> 02:02:58,373
Yes.

1870
02:02:58,498 --> 02:03:00,914
Hey! Basha, Jani, Khatri, Ahmed!

1871
02:03:01,164 --> 02:03:04,581
His legs, arms, neck, and torso…
hack them into pieces

1872
02:03:04,664 --> 02:03:07,748
and decide whether you
want to cremate or bury them.

1873
02:03:13,164 --> 02:03:15,373
While they decide,
could you get me some water?

1874
02:03:20,289 --> 02:03:21,289
Hey, Chotu!

1875
02:03:22,831 --> 02:03:24,373
Have you ever played Thief and Police?

1876
02:03:24,706 --> 02:03:26,039
Police don't come here, brother.

1877
02:03:26,831 --> 02:03:28,039
But the black guard is here.

1878
02:03:39,123 --> 02:03:40,248
Do you want to watch the game?

1879
02:04:17,206 --> 02:04:19,123
What are you looking at, sisters?

1880
02:04:21,831 --> 02:04:23,539
I will get him down.

1881
02:04:24,123 --> 02:04:25,331
You please get down to cooking.

1882
02:04:29,956 --> 02:04:31,664
The biryani should be delicious, sister.

1883
02:04:32,289 --> 02:04:33,373
Make it spicy.

1884
02:05:13,873 --> 02:05:15,123
Why do you stare?

1885
02:05:16,873 --> 02:05:18,373
Is the cigarette appearing in 3D?

1886
02:06:06,664 --> 02:06:10,248
Oh, my! Brother Das!

1887
02:06:10,789 --> 02:06:12,998
Oh, my! Brother Das!

1888
02:06:13,456 --> 02:06:15,831
What a tragedy!

1889
02:06:16,664 --> 02:06:17,664
Hey!

1890
02:06:17,831 --> 02:06:19,123
What do we do now?

1891
02:06:19,289 --> 02:06:21,623
I don't mind holding you by your hair
and smashing you to the ground!

1892
02:06:27,873 --> 02:06:28,956
What is happening, Uncle?

1893
02:06:30,123 --> 02:06:31,123
Are you Das?

1894
02:06:32,456 --> 02:06:33,373
Yes.

1895
02:06:37,748 --> 02:06:39,914
- What about him?
- He sells fritters.

1896
02:06:40,123 --> 02:06:41,248
Why were you sitting outside?

1897
02:06:42,289 --> 02:06:44,998
Whenever someone comes,
I sit at the fritter shop,

1898
02:06:45,123 --> 02:06:47,081
and he sits in my chair.

1899
02:06:47,164 --> 02:06:48,248
Oh, my!

1900
02:06:48,498 --> 02:06:49,414
But why?

1901
02:06:50,539 --> 02:06:51,914
To elude.

1902
02:06:57,998 --> 02:07:00,581
I saw such tricks long ago in old films.

1903
02:07:01,789 --> 02:07:03,331
And now, I see you.

1904
02:07:04,831 --> 02:07:06,331
It really hurts.

1905
02:07:06,706 --> 02:07:08,081
I'm not able to bear it.

1906
02:07:09,039 --> 02:07:11,081
What sin have I committed, God?

1907
02:07:11,164 --> 02:07:12,081
Shall I tell you?

1908
02:07:13,748 --> 02:07:15,123
Threatening the minister.

1909
02:07:16,123 --> 02:07:18,664
Ramming a truck into their car
while they are inside.

1910
02:07:19,039 --> 02:07:22,789
God may be busy, but sons like me,
who gallivant with no work…

1911
02:07:23,956 --> 02:07:25,289
will come looking for you.

1912
02:07:26,581 --> 02:07:28,789
Why would I kill your mother?

1913
02:07:29,164 --> 02:07:30,873
I have only threatened her.

1914
02:07:31,414 --> 02:07:34,539
My problem is only… with your grandfather.

1915
02:07:35,998 --> 02:07:37,581
What has the old man done to you?

1916
02:07:37,998 --> 02:07:41,081
If I recall that, I will die right away.
Why remember that mess now?

1917
02:07:41,164 --> 02:07:43,373
Hey! You brainless morons!

1918
02:07:43,581 --> 02:07:45,581
Stop crying and pull this out.

1919
02:07:46,206 --> 02:07:47,081
Wait.

1920
02:07:47,456 --> 02:07:49,248
Hey! Sister!

1921
02:07:50,498 --> 02:07:52,414
- What are you trying to pull?
- Why?

1922
02:07:55,414 --> 02:07:57,039
I think it has pierced
right through the center.

1923
02:07:58,248 --> 02:08:01,373
If you pull it, blood will gush out
like water from a borewell.

1924
02:08:03,164 --> 02:08:04,998
At least suture it.

1925
02:08:05,123 --> 02:08:07,164
If I was so skilled, why would I be here?

1926
02:08:07,664 --> 02:08:10,789
Like KIMS and NIMS,
I would have set up GUMS in Guntur.

1927
02:08:13,664 --> 02:08:14,956
Only God can save you now.

1928
02:08:15,039 --> 02:08:16,248
Forget God!

1929
02:08:16,831 --> 02:08:18,581
There is not even a doctor here.

1930
02:08:19,581 --> 02:08:22,206
You are set up in a jungle
and talk as if Apollo is next door!

1931
02:08:22,498 --> 02:08:25,664
You are right.
Hey, call the ambulance at least.

1932
02:08:27,039 --> 02:08:28,289
We don't have the number, brother.

1933
02:08:30,998 --> 02:08:32,331
It's all over, sisters.

1934
02:08:32,873 --> 02:08:34,164
Go and comb
your hair, all of you.

1935
02:08:39,831 --> 02:08:40,789
Hey, Balu!

1936
02:08:51,789 --> 02:08:53,581
Have you got a doctor for me, Kata?

1937
02:08:53,664 --> 02:08:55,206
No, Dasu. I have brought him.

1938
02:08:56,998 --> 02:08:59,581
- Are you fine?
- Look who you gave my address to!

1939
02:09:03,373 --> 02:09:05,706
I'm the victim.
Why is the nurse looking at him?

1940
02:09:05,789 --> 02:09:06,998
That's his love, not a nurse.

1941
02:09:08,581 --> 02:09:10,081
She's the nurse. Do something.

1942
02:09:10,248 --> 02:09:11,373
Who pierced the nail through?

1943
02:09:13,539 --> 02:09:15,581
Wow! Great person!

1944
02:09:15,789 --> 02:09:17,164
He has given you a second life.

1945
02:09:17,414 --> 02:09:21,706
I don't even have to put a stent.
98 percent of the valves were blocked.

1946
02:09:21,789 --> 02:09:23,206
By piercing with a nail,
he opened all of them.

1947
02:09:23,414 --> 02:09:24,748
But you need some blood.

1948
02:09:24,873 --> 02:09:26,164
B positive, doctor.

1949
02:09:26,248 --> 02:09:28,414
I'm definitely positive.
I'm asking for your blood group.

1950
02:09:28,706 --> 02:09:30,831
That's what I told you, doctor.
B positive!

1951
02:09:30,914 --> 02:09:31,998
But who will give the blood?

1952
02:09:32,248 --> 02:09:34,289
Hey! One of you come forward.

1953
02:09:34,498 --> 02:09:35,498
Come on, brother!

1954
02:09:35,623 --> 02:09:37,914
How can we have blood?
It's all brandy.

1955
02:09:38,289 --> 02:09:39,831
In that case,
remove the nail during cremation.

1956
02:09:39,914 --> 02:09:42,248
- Brother Das!
- Hey!

1957
02:09:42,373 --> 02:09:44,331
Stop it, stop it!

1958
02:09:44,414 --> 02:09:45,373
Oh, my!

1959
02:09:45,664 --> 02:09:47,539
Why do you start crying?

1960
02:09:47,748 --> 02:09:49,623
One of you just donate blood.

1961
02:09:52,456 --> 02:09:55,914
The one who stabbed him is donating
his blood. This is a historical moment.

1962
02:09:59,039 --> 02:10:00,623
Keep these things aside, Uncle.

1963
02:10:01,748 --> 02:10:02,914
What is your problem with my grandpa?

1964
02:10:03,331 --> 02:10:06,164
Both of us were into business together
25 years ago.

1965
02:10:06,414 --> 02:10:08,373
We got double returns.

1966
02:10:08,998 --> 02:10:10,581
What should the ratio be?

1967
02:10:10,789 --> 02:10:13,789
To be all fair and honest… fifty each?

1968
02:10:14,998 --> 02:10:17,873
He wanted ten percent more
since it was his idea.

1969
02:10:18,289 --> 02:10:19,248
Fair enough.

1970
02:10:19,748 --> 02:10:21,206
But you should get at least forty.

1971
02:10:21,331 --> 02:10:22,623
Claiming ownership of goodwill,

1972
02:10:22,706 --> 02:10:24,914
he insisted on an additional
ten percent as interest.

1973
02:10:24,998 --> 02:10:25,914
Tough!

1974
02:10:26,456 --> 02:10:27,664
Did he at least give you thirty?

1975
02:10:27,873 --> 02:10:31,831
Since supply had to continue, he sought
an additional ten percent for investment.

1976
02:10:32,164 --> 02:10:33,123
Terrible!

1977
02:10:33,581 --> 02:10:34,873
He should at least give you twenty.

1978
02:10:34,956 --> 02:10:38,331
He said I'd squander the money at once.
So, he wanted to pay in two installments.

1979
02:10:38,414 --> 02:10:39,414
Glad.

1980
02:10:39,914 --> 02:10:40,914
What about the ten percent?

1981
02:10:40,998 --> 02:10:43,914
He gave me five,
and when I asked him about the rest,

1982
02:10:44,081 --> 02:10:47,248
he called me rowdy
and kicked me out.

1983
02:10:49,831 --> 02:10:51,831
He showed you fifty percent profit
and gave you only five?

1984
02:10:51,998 --> 02:10:53,956
I wasn't hurt by that.

1985
02:10:54,206 --> 02:10:56,081
Do you know
what he did when I was leaving?

1986
02:10:57,331 --> 02:10:58,664
He gave this to me.

1987
02:11:01,164 --> 02:11:02,956
I knew that the old man was nasty.

1988
02:11:04,331 --> 02:11:05,748
I just didn't know how nasty!

1989
02:11:07,081 --> 02:11:08,039
Don't worry.

1990
02:11:08,706 --> 02:11:10,289
I will be the gun under your pillow.

1991
02:11:10,956 --> 02:11:12,039
Just give me a call.

1992
02:11:12,789 --> 02:11:13,706
I will be there.

1993
02:11:14,664 --> 02:11:15,539
Stop!

1994
02:11:17,914 --> 02:11:20,206
How can you donate blood
and just walk away?

1995
02:11:21,164 --> 02:11:22,414
You can't always have your way.

1996
02:11:23,373 --> 02:11:25,164
Let us at least throw you a party.

1997
02:11:26,914 --> 02:11:27,831
Hey!

1998
02:11:28,331 --> 02:11:29,873
Call our Ramola batch.

1999
02:11:36,831 --> 02:11:38,956
Young lad, pass me the chilled water.

2000
02:11:43,373 --> 02:11:45,789
Salutations to the theater!

2001
02:11:46,206 --> 02:11:49,539
A grand welcome to connoisseurs!

2002
02:11:50,081 --> 02:11:53,748
The time is seven o'clock
The evening is dusky

2003
02:11:53,831 --> 02:11:56,956
The cool breeze begins to tickle

2004
02:11:57,206 --> 02:12:03,248
Daring Das seated on that couch
And the elegant prince on this one

2005
02:12:03,331 --> 02:12:09,539
Ramola dancing party's performance

2006
02:12:09,789 --> 02:12:11,456
Why don't we make it scintillating?

2007
02:12:11,789 --> 02:12:12,789
Hey, Ramola!

2008
02:12:13,039 --> 02:12:14,664
Why don't we drape this girl in a sari?

2009
02:12:32,789 --> 02:12:34,706
Ragamanjari from Rajahmundry

2010
02:12:34,789 --> 02:12:38,081
There's no one
Who doesn't know the mother of me

2011
02:12:38,623 --> 02:12:44,081
All are artists in the family
With our dance, we commit sleep robbery

2012
02:12:50,248 --> 02:12:55,581
Stylish, dream girl!
Your velvety look is a bed of jasmines

2013
02:12:56,081 --> 02:13:01,789
My breath is on fire
Looking at you makes my heart go crazy

2014
02:13:07,748 --> 02:13:13,206
Loading bullets in your curves
You fired shots, my belle

2015
02:13:13,289 --> 02:13:15,498
Seducing the entire male race…

2016
02:13:16,498 --> 02:13:18,081
Folding the chair…

2017
02:13:18,373 --> 02:13:22,664
Folding the chair…
Folding it…

2018
02:13:22,748 --> 02:13:25,581
Folding it…
Folding it…

2019
02:13:54,664 --> 02:13:57,456
To her…

2020
02:13:57,581 --> 02:14:02,914
To her, you gifted the goats
And gave me broken rice

2021
02:14:03,373 --> 02:14:09,539
The goats grew into hundreds and herds
And my broken rice melted in titbits

2022
02:14:11,789 --> 02:14:17,456
You gave her emerald earrings
You gave me dotted, checkered saris

2023
02:14:17,956 --> 02:14:23,748
Her earrings shone with sparkles
My saris turned into tatters

2024
02:14:23,831 --> 02:14:29,414
What sort of patron are you, Mr. Das?
You are always with prejudice!

2025
02:14:29,498 --> 02:14:35,289
What sort of patron are you, Mr. Das?
You are always with prejudice!

2026
02:14:35,414 --> 02:14:36,789
Folding the chair…

2027
02:14:36,873 --> 02:14:39,706
Folding it…
Folding it…

2028
02:14:39,789 --> 02:14:43,664
Folding it…
Folding it…

2029
02:14:58,623 --> 02:15:02,373
Such a stylish, beautiful lady

2030
02:15:03,039 --> 02:15:05,248
Your velvety look is a bed of jasmines

2031
02:15:05,873 --> 02:15:08,206
My breath is on fire

2032
02:15:08,873 --> 02:15:11,914
Looking at you makes my heart go crazy

2033
02:15:23,373 --> 02:15:24,539
What are you looking at?

2034
02:15:24,831 --> 02:15:26,789
Each one is a lyric writer
of his own anguish.

2035
02:15:27,248 --> 02:15:29,164
Write it, fold it, and throw it.

2036
02:15:29,248 --> 02:15:32,039
Folding it…

2037
02:15:32,123 --> 02:15:34,956
Folding it…

2038
02:15:35,039 --> 02:15:39,373
Folding it…

2039
02:15:39,456 --> 02:15:40,873
Folding the chair…

2040
02:15:42,414 --> 02:15:43,831
Folding it…

2041
02:15:45,206 --> 02:15:46,706
Folding it…

2042
02:15:48,206 --> 02:15:49,789
Folding it…

2043
02:15:54,539 --> 02:15:55,539
Just one word.

2044
02:15:56,206 --> 02:15:57,373
It's a bloody cult mass song!

2045
02:15:58,414 --> 02:16:00,581
- Long live…
- Janadalam party!

2046
02:16:00,664 --> 02:16:02,414
- Long live…
- Janadalam party!

2047
02:16:02,498 --> 02:16:04,539
- Long live…
- Janadalam party!

2048
02:16:04,623 --> 02:16:06,831
- Long live…
- Vyra Venkata Swamy!

2049
02:16:06,914 --> 02:16:09,164
- Long live…
- Sir.

2050
02:16:09,248 --> 02:16:11,331
- Long live…
- Vyra Venkata Swamy!

2051
02:16:11,539 --> 02:16:13,664
- Long live…
- Please wait.

2052
02:16:14,039 --> 02:16:15,581
Enough. Okay.

2053
02:16:16,039 --> 02:16:17,123
What? It's a book.

2054
02:16:18,206 --> 02:16:19,664
Okay, okay. Move.

2055
02:16:20,498 --> 02:16:22,456
- Where is Raja Gopal?
- Didn't he come with you, sir?

2056
02:16:23,164 --> 02:16:24,998
- Long live…
- Vyra Venkata Swamy!

2057
02:16:25,456 --> 02:16:27,873
- Long live…
- Vyra Venkata Swamy!

2058
02:16:28,873 --> 02:16:29,956
- Gopal sir!
- Gopal.

2059
02:16:30,164 --> 02:16:31,623
Where's Gopal sir? Have you seen him?

2060
02:16:31,831 --> 02:16:32,789
Gopal!

2061
02:16:33,331 --> 02:16:34,206
Gopal sir!

2062
02:16:35,664 --> 02:16:36,998
- Gopal sir!
- Narayana!

2063
02:16:38,331 --> 02:16:40,039
- Gopal sir!
- Narayana!

2064
02:16:41,956 --> 02:16:42,998
Drunkard…

2065
02:16:43,373 --> 02:16:44,664
Hey!

2066
02:16:45,289 --> 02:16:46,706
- Uncle?
- Where is he?

2067
02:16:47,706 --> 02:16:49,289
- Who, Uncle?
- Who else?

2068
02:16:49,373 --> 02:16:50,956
- Your own son!
- My son…

2069
02:16:51,039 --> 02:16:52,206
He has left home.

2070
02:16:52,289 --> 02:16:53,831
But he's nowhere to be found.
Where is he?

2071
02:16:54,706 --> 02:16:56,623
He must be somewhere around, Uncle.

2072
02:16:56,914 --> 02:16:58,248
Oh, there he is!

2073
02:17:01,414 --> 02:17:02,373
What did you do?

2074
02:17:02,831 --> 02:17:03,706
Actually, Uncle…

2075
02:17:04,123 --> 02:17:05,289
He has joined the Party.

2076
02:17:05,664 --> 02:17:07,206
He's also getting the MP ticket.

2077
02:17:07,331 --> 02:17:08,956
He said he was feeling nervous…

2078
02:17:09,039 --> 02:17:09,956
So?

2079
02:17:10,664 --> 02:17:13,831
To pep him up,
I gave him a glass of juice, Uncle.

2080
02:17:14,248 --> 02:17:15,331
Oh, no!

2081
02:17:16,081 --> 02:17:17,123
Hey, Gopal!

2082
02:17:18,581 --> 02:17:19,748
I think he's in a stupor.

2083
02:17:19,998 --> 02:17:22,164
Uncle, I will get him ready
in ten minutes.

2084
02:17:22,373 --> 02:17:23,706
Hey! Someone get some buttermilk!

2085
02:17:23,789 --> 02:17:25,123
You should be killed, wastrel!

2086
02:17:25,289 --> 02:17:27,123
- I will not spare you!
- Uncle!

2087
02:17:27,206 --> 02:17:28,498
- Die!
- Uncle!

2088
02:17:28,998 --> 02:17:29,873
- I was…
- Uncle!

2089
02:17:29,956 --> 02:17:33,248
I was going to make him join the Party,
but you organized your own party!

2090
02:17:33,331 --> 02:17:36,539
- And today of all the days!
- Uncle! What did I do?

2091
02:17:36,623 --> 02:17:39,539
He is the future of this family
and politics!

2092
02:17:39,623 --> 02:17:41,039
- Not a wastrel like you!
- Uncle!

2093
02:17:41,331 --> 02:17:43,831
He is Vyra Venkata Swamy's heir!

2094
02:17:44,039 --> 02:17:45,789
Who? Who is the heir?

2095
02:17:46,581 --> 02:17:47,914
He is not even my son!

2096
02:17:48,706 --> 02:17:49,956
I don't even have a son!

2097
02:17:58,581 --> 02:17:59,623
I don't even have a son!

2098
02:18:01,414 --> 02:18:04,498
Whether you like it or not,
you have only one heir!

2099
02:18:07,956 --> 02:18:09,873
Bhogineni Veera Venkata Ramana!

2100
02:18:17,331 --> 02:18:18,539
He is your real heir!

2101
02:18:35,164 --> 02:18:37,331
Are you so drunk
that you are blabbering?

2102
02:18:38,498 --> 02:18:39,414
Me?

2103
02:18:42,873 --> 02:18:44,498
Exactly 25 years ago…

2104
02:18:45,664 --> 02:18:47,831
your daughter married a man
from a different caste.

2105
02:18:49,164 --> 02:18:50,498
You had told me when
you lost the election.

2106
02:18:51,623 --> 02:18:55,081
By the time the next elections occurred,
you pulled the strings.

2107
02:18:56,831 --> 02:19:00,789
Now, just as your grandson
is about to enter politics,

2108
02:19:00,873 --> 02:19:02,414
your daughter is pulling the strings.

2109
02:19:04,873 --> 02:19:09,289
Your daughter didn't marry me
because she thought I was handsome.

2110
02:19:10,664 --> 02:19:12,581
She married me to make a fool of you.

2111
02:19:15,748 --> 02:19:18,123
Fortunately, since our bedroom
is on the first floor,

2112
02:19:18,539 --> 02:19:20,039
you're unable to climb the stairs.

2113
02:19:20,831 --> 02:19:23,581
Let me tell you
that there are two beds in there.

2114
02:19:24,498 --> 02:19:26,914
You can place a net between them
and play badminton.

2115
02:19:27,164 --> 02:19:28,206
That's the situation.

2116
02:19:29,748 --> 02:19:32,581
As soon as you began to wonder
why there were no children yet,

2117
02:19:32,664 --> 02:19:33,623
she announced her pregnancy.

2118
02:19:34,164 --> 02:19:36,914
She said she would be more comfortable
delivering the baby abroad,

2119
02:19:36,998 --> 02:19:38,581
and went to Aunt Raji in Australia.

2120
02:19:38,956 --> 02:19:39,998
Once she reached there,

2121
02:19:40,081 --> 02:19:42,998
she said she didn't want to trouble them
and stayed alone.

2122
02:19:43,414 --> 02:19:46,914
Have you even seen her photograph
when she was pregnant?

2123
02:19:50,206 --> 02:19:51,081
No.

2124
02:19:51,748 --> 02:19:52,623
Right.

2125
02:19:53,206 --> 02:19:54,581
She came back with him.

2126
02:19:55,331 --> 02:19:56,289
You took him.

2127
02:19:56,581 --> 02:19:57,706
Carried him on your back.

2128
02:19:58,206 --> 02:19:59,498
When he cried, you called it music!

2129
02:19:59,956 --> 02:20:01,331
When he peed, you called it perfume!

2130
02:20:02,164 --> 02:20:06,081
If you gave him my surname "Pakka",
you thought he would be sidelined.

2131
02:20:06,373 --> 02:20:08,331
So, you call him Vyra Rajagopal!

2132
02:20:08,998 --> 02:20:10,248
You are making him an MP now.

2133
02:20:11,081 --> 02:20:13,289
If all goes well, you would like
to reverse it and make him the PM.

2134
02:20:16,123 --> 02:20:19,414
But if you realize
he is not your daughter's son…

2135
02:20:21,623 --> 02:20:22,498
what will you do?

2136
02:20:25,998 --> 02:20:27,998
Your daughter is not boastful
like you, Uncle.

2137
02:20:28,081 --> 02:20:29,039
No way!

2138
02:20:30,164 --> 02:20:31,539
She sent her husband to jail.

2139
02:20:32,289 --> 02:20:33,581
You trusted her 25 percent.

2140
02:20:34,248 --> 02:20:36,831
She married me.
You trusted her 50 percent.

2141
02:20:37,289 --> 02:20:38,414
She said she gave birth to him.

2142
02:20:38,623 --> 02:20:40,039
You trusted her 75 percent.

2143
02:20:40,331 --> 02:20:41,664
She abandoned her own son.

2144
02:20:43,289 --> 02:20:44,414
You trusted her a hundred percent!

2145
02:20:46,623 --> 02:20:51,081
She has proved that a mother would go
to any extent to protect her son. Wow!

2146
02:20:52,539 --> 02:20:54,039
Your daughter is not
an ordinary woman, Uncle.

2147
02:21:01,581 --> 02:21:05,206
She can easily manipulate three men
like you into following her plan!

2148
02:21:05,998 --> 02:21:07,123
You should have told me this earlier…

2149
02:21:07,956 --> 02:21:13,873
Actually, once you cross 70, people
like you shouldn't stay alive, Uncle.

2150
02:21:14,414 --> 02:21:15,498
You must make your exit.

2151
02:21:16,623 --> 02:21:17,539
You should.

2152
02:21:17,789 --> 02:21:19,373
That would do good to everyone.

2153
02:21:19,998 --> 02:21:20,956
Please die, father-in-law.

2154
02:21:21,331 --> 02:21:22,914
- Heed my advice.
- Grandpa! Careful!

2155
02:21:23,414 --> 02:21:25,206
Hey! Who is your grandpa?

2156
02:21:28,123 --> 02:21:29,164
Who is your grandpa?

2157
02:21:32,039 --> 02:21:34,664
All of you are playing a game
behind my back, right?

2158
02:21:35,248 --> 02:21:36,289
I'm going to kill you.

2159
02:21:37,414 --> 02:21:38,831
She's the one behind you, right?

2160
02:21:39,623 --> 02:21:41,873
She should be killed first.

2161
02:21:43,414 --> 02:21:45,373
In that case,
you should be killed a hundred times.

2162
02:21:48,956 --> 02:21:50,081
I couldn't stop him, sir.

2163
02:21:53,623 --> 02:21:54,539
What's with you?

2164
02:21:56,164 --> 02:21:58,081
You walked in quietly like a fake voter?

2165
02:22:02,206 --> 02:22:03,581
I was missing you.

2166
02:22:05,331 --> 02:22:06,289
So, I have come to talk.

2167
02:22:06,414 --> 02:22:08,498
I would also like to talk.
Come. Let's talk.

2168
02:22:08,581 --> 02:22:09,914
Hey, get a chair. Come on.

2169
02:22:10,373 --> 02:22:14,373
Normally, people discuss their kids'
future. We'll discuss your mom's past.

2170
02:22:14,456 --> 02:22:15,498
Come on!

2171
02:22:16,914 --> 02:22:18,706
Is your mom some goddess in a temple?

2172
02:22:19,039 --> 02:22:20,664
You want to visit her all the time!

2173
02:22:21,581 --> 02:22:22,623
She's a demon!

2174
02:22:25,789 --> 02:22:27,123
Why did you orchestrate the accident?

2175
02:22:27,373 --> 02:22:28,373
Which accident?

2176
02:22:28,581 --> 02:22:30,581
The one in which you made a truck
ram into her car?

2177
02:22:34,956 --> 02:22:36,706
Hey, get me some water.

2178
02:22:37,164 --> 02:22:38,164
That accident.

2179
02:22:38,498 --> 02:22:39,664
Ask Hari Das!

2180
02:22:42,664 --> 02:22:43,623
Hey!

2181
02:22:47,248 --> 02:22:48,414
Give him the glass, Dasu.

2182
02:22:50,539 --> 02:22:51,706
Why are you shocked?

2183
02:22:53,456 --> 02:22:54,414
It's our very own Das.

2184
02:22:54,914 --> 02:22:57,039
Don't clean the blood on your hands
with the water he gave you.

2185
02:22:59,581 --> 02:23:00,789
Whose truck was it?

2186
02:23:01,248 --> 02:23:02,414
Aren't there enough rogues?

2187
02:23:02,873 --> 02:23:04,456
If not him, it must have been Madhu's job!

2188
02:23:05,581 --> 02:23:07,081
You could fall. Careful.

2189
02:23:22,873 --> 02:23:24,623
As a precaution, I have brought him along.

2190
02:23:25,664 --> 02:23:27,206
Please don't say
he was behind the accident.

2191
02:23:27,539 --> 02:23:29,248
Because he himself is ramming
into things and falling.

2192
02:23:31,456 --> 02:23:32,539
Why did you do it?

2193
02:23:34,498 --> 02:23:37,498
Do you think it is easy to win
the fourth time after three terms?

2194
02:23:38,248 --> 02:23:39,664
There has to be some magic.

2195
02:23:42,373 --> 02:23:44,956
I organized a murder attempt.
I created sympathy.

2196
02:23:45,414 --> 02:23:46,539
Go, check the surveys.

2197
02:23:46,956 --> 02:23:48,123
They confirm her victory.

2198
02:23:49,164 --> 02:23:50,623
Anyway, what is the problem now?

2199
02:23:52,081 --> 02:23:53,164
She is not dead…

2200
02:23:53,831 --> 02:23:54,748
Uncle!

2201
02:23:57,956 --> 02:24:02,414
A little harder and there won't be
any need for surveys.

2202
02:24:03,539 --> 02:24:05,456
She's sure to secure victory
through sympathy.

2203
02:24:20,331 --> 02:24:22,039
As soon as you discovered
he was not your grandson,

2204
02:24:22,123 --> 02:24:23,539
you discarded him asking
who his grandfather is!

2205
02:24:24,123 --> 02:24:26,539
But she raised him
like her own son for thirty years.

2206
02:24:26,956 --> 02:24:28,956
Hey, I'm not jealous of you.
Please don't feel bad.

2207
02:24:32,123 --> 02:24:33,998
Her action was betrayal,
and yours was sacrifice.

2208
02:24:36,914 --> 02:24:39,789
Shall I give you a list of her sacrifices?
Your heart will stop.

2209
02:24:41,289 --> 02:24:42,539
A pointless wedding.

2210
02:24:43,623 --> 02:24:44,748
A meaningless marriage.

2211
02:24:47,373 --> 02:24:48,373
A son who's not her own.

2212
02:24:49,914 --> 02:24:51,081
And an unsolicited rank.

2213
02:24:52,331 --> 02:24:53,456
For whom did she do all this?

2214
02:24:54,623 --> 02:24:56,123
She did it so that Ramana
could live like a king!

2215
02:24:58,123 --> 02:24:59,164
I failed to understand then.

2216
02:24:59,873 --> 02:25:00,831
I'm a dunderhead!

2217
02:25:02,539 --> 02:25:03,748
I'm not sure if you said it
knowingly or not…

2218
02:25:04,123 --> 02:25:05,039
but she is truly a goddess.

2219
02:25:05,664 --> 02:25:06,664
Any place she is becomes a temple.

2220
02:25:08,123 --> 02:25:10,081
When she leaves tomorrow,
you will know, Venkata Swamy.

2221
02:25:10,748 --> 02:25:12,206
Forget about a sacred offering,

2222
02:25:12,706 --> 02:25:14,289
there won't be a soul
who would offer you a flower.

2223
02:25:27,664 --> 02:25:29,414
With so much love in your heart,

2224
02:25:30,289 --> 02:25:31,248
you choose to fight.

2225
02:25:32,623 --> 02:25:34,539
Is shouting Ramana's way
of expressing love?

2226
02:25:35,498 --> 02:25:36,373
Come.

2227
02:25:37,373 --> 02:25:40,706
You have done whatever you want,
and now look at you talking!

2228
02:25:41,248 --> 02:25:42,539
What have I done, Dad?

2229
02:25:43,414 --> 02:25:44,831
Did I set the warehouses on fire?

2230
02:25:45,373 --> 02:25:46,456
Did I organize murders?

2231
02:25:47,831 --> 02:25:49,331
I just wanted him to do well.

2232
02:25:49,581 --> 02:25:50,581
Is that a crime?

2233
02:25:52,331 --> 02:25:55,456
You've arranged for a survey
on election result trends if I die.

2234
02:25:56,456 --> 02:25:58,748
Now that I'm leaving,
get a fresh survey done.

2235
02:25:58,831 --> 02:25:59,914
Where will you go?

2236
02:26:00,998 --> 02:26:01,873
If you go,

2237
02:26:01,956 --> 02:26:04,831
I'll kill everyone in that place
and not even leave an address to refer to.

2238
02:26:05,164 --> 02:26:07,456
You're threatening me
even after you saw him?

2239
02:26:08,664 --> 02:26:10,331
Back then, he was as tall as your knee.

2240
02:26:11,039 --> 02:26:12,873
Now, he has made you kneel!

2241
02:26:13,248 --> 02:26:14,248
What the heck?

2242
02:26:14,664 --> 02:26:16,498
Why are you talking nonsense like him?

2243
02:26:17,456 --> 02:26:19,456
Why would I talk like him, Dad?

2244
02:26:20,248 --> 02:26:21,873
He talks like me.

2245
02:26:22,956 --> 02:26:24,498
Because he is my son.

2246
02:26:27,956 --> 02:26:28,873
Son!

2247
02:26:29,039 --> 02:26:30,498
What do you mean by son?

2248
02:26:34,498 --> 02:26:35,581
You can say that again.

2249
02:26:37,914 --> 02:26:39,081
You are my son.

2250
02:26:45,956 --> 02:26:47,123
Why didn't you tell me all these years?

2251
02:26:48,539 --> 02:26:51,164
Do you think love is confined
to inquiries about food and sleep?

2252
02:26:56,956 --> 02:26:58,164
When I came home, I was kicked out.

2253
02:26:58,873 --> 02:27:00,248
But I watched you from upstairs.

2254
02:27:04,623 --> 02:27:05,748
You slapped me
as soon as you saw me.

2255
02:27:06,373 --> 02:27:07,664
I wanted to touch you.

2256
02:27:11,748 --> 02:27:13,081
At the hospital, you said
you didn't like me.

2257
02:27:14,248 --> 02:27:16,456
Before that, I mentioned
my favorite things, didn't I?

2258
02:27:17,539 --> 02:27:18,539
Before what?

2259
02:27:19,706 --> 02:27:20,581
Hey!

2260
02:27:21,581 --> 02:27:23,331
When you were a child,
you used to bother me about food.

2261
02:27:24,581 --> 02:27:26,206
Now, you want to trouble me
about talking?

2262
02:27:28,123 --> 02:27:30,206
A mother would have to die
before she leaves her son.

2263
02:27:43,206 --> 02:27:44,664
Bloody hell, Venkata Swamy!

2264
02:27:46,123 --> 02:27:48,748
Waiting another 25 years
to hear this again would be worthwhile.

2265
02:27:50,831 --> 02:27:52,664
When she speaks,
it's not just my ears that listen,

2266
02:27:53,706 --> 02:27:55,081
but my entire body.

2267
02:27:55,956 --> 02:27:56,998
- Hey!
- Hey!

2268
02:27:57,123 --> 02:27:58,706
Why do you want to talk to him?
Come on.

2269
02:27:59,706 --> 02:28:00,581
Hey!

2270
02:28:01,498 --> 02:28:02,664
Wait!

2271
02:28:02,956 --> 02:28:03,831
Wait!

2272
02:28:07,581 --> 02:28:09,498
Hey!

2273
02:28:17,956 --> 02:28:19,081
Long live…

2274
02:28:20,164 --> 02:28:21,414
Long live…

2275
02:28:22,748 --> 02:28:23,789
Long live…

2276
02:29:33,539 --> 02:29:34,456
What is it?

2277
02:29:38,414 --> 02:29:39,539
As soon as I saw you…

2278
02:29:41,039 --> 02:29:42,206
I wanted to pick a big fight.

2279
02:29:44,248 --> 02:29:45,956
But the moment you touched me,
I forgot everything.

2280
02:29:49,873 --> 02:29:50,748
What?

2281
02:29:51,331 --> 02:29:52,456
You are so handsome.

2282
02:29:53,498 --> 02:29:55,248
- Why the beard?
- This?

2283
02:29:57,914 --> 02:29:58,873
Love failure.

2284
02:30:00,456 --> 02:30:01,331
Hey!

2285
02:30:01,789 --> 02:30:02,706
Who is the girl?

2286
02:30:06,206 --> 02:30:07,081
You.

2287
02:30:14,039 --> 02:30:15,789
Hey, when did you come?

2288
02:30:28,456 --> 02:30:29,414
Bujji…

2289
02:30:36,539 --> 02:30:37,539
How are you?

2290
02:30:44,164 --> 02:30:45,123
Bujji!

2291
02:30:45,248 --> 02:30:46,623
Bujji… Bujji!

2292
02:31:40,789 --> 02:31:42,164
How are you, Satyam?

2293
02:31:44,123 --> 02:31:45,206
How are you?

2294
02:31:49,914 --> 02:31:50,873
My room…

2295
02:31:53,873 --> 02:31:54,998
your memories…

2296
02:31:58,081 --> 02:31:59,664
Here… like this…

2297
02:32:22,914 --> 02:32:23,956
Old songs…

2298
02:32:25,123 --> 02:32:26,206
Old bike…

2299
02:32:28,831 --> 02:32:29,831
Old wife…

2300
02:32:33,248 --> 02:32:34,289
I didn't give up anything.

2301
02:32:40,248 --> 02:32:44,748
Did it take you so long
to stop being angry with me?

2302
02:32:47,664 --> 02:32:52,539
It took me so many years
to stop being afraid of my dad.

2303
02:33:17,081 --> 02:33:18,831
You were so hurt
that you had shut the door on her.

2304
02:33:21,123 --> 02:33:22,373
Today, you opened
the door to her yourself.

2305
02:33:23,164 --> 02:33:24,248
Is it even?

2306
02:33:37,123 --> 02:33:38,331
- Hey, Samba!
- Yes?

2307
02:33:39,164 --> 02:33:40,664
Shall I give you a nice caption?

2308
02:33:42,289 --> 02:33:43,414
"Ramana is rebellious…

2309
02:33:44,456 --> 02:33:45,664
because he has two mothers."

2310
02:34:09,123 --> 02:34:10,831
Uncle! Venkata Swamy is calling.

2311
02:34:15,081 --> 02:34:16,331
Cut the call and block him.

2312
02:34:22,289 --> 02:34:25,123
All this while you have been sharpening
a needle instead of a knife.

2313
02:34:25,873 --> 02:34:27,623
I will start sharpening
the knife then.

2314
02:34:27,873 --> 02:34:28,748
Uncle…

2315
02:34:28,831 --> 02:34:30,789
My constituency should not be orphaned.

2316
02:34:31,289 --> 02:34:32,539
We need Ramana.

2317
02:34:32,914 --> 02:34:34,081
He won't come.
It's a waste of time.

2318
02:34:34,248 --> 02:34:35,539
What would bring him to us?

2319
02:34:35,873 --> 02:34:36,831
Uncle…

2320
02:34:37,206 --> 02:34:39,873
during every festival, we decorate
with festoons made of mango leaves.

2321
02:34:40,539 --> 02:34:42,164
It's considered auspicious, right?

2322
02:34:42,373 --> 02:34:43,789
After a few days, the leaves dry up,

2323
02:34:43,873 --> 02:34:47,456
and the rustling sound they make
becomes irritating to the ear.

2324
02:34:48,123 --> 02:34:51,414
We can't discard it
due to sentimental reasons.

2325
02:34:52,373 --> 02:34:53,873
You are just like that, Uncle.

2326
02:34:54,164 --> 02:34:56,956
Discarding you would be a sin
while keeping you would pose a risk.

2327
02:34:57,414 --> 02:34:59,081
Drop the matter.
It's a waste of time.

2328
02:35:13,664 --> 02:35:15,164
- He isn't home.
- I know.

2329
02:35:15,331 --> 02:35:16,206
Wow!

2330
02:35:16,289 --> 02:35:17,164
Hi, sir.

2331
02:35:17,414 --> 02:35:18,331
- Hey!
- Sir?

2332
02:35:18,456 --> 02:35:20,164
- Are those clothes?
- Yes, sir.

2333
02:35:20,456 --> 02:35:22,206
- Bought or tailored?
- Ready-made, sir.

2334
02:35:23,539 --> 02:35:24,539
Shall we go?

2335
02:35:24,914 --> 02:35:25,831
Where to, sir?

2336
02:35:25,998 --> 02:35:26,998
What do you care?

2337
02:35:27,289 --> 02:35:28,456
When will you be back, sir?

2338
02:35:28,914 --> 02:35:30,706
- Tomorrow evening.
- Tomorrow evening?

2339
02:35:31,206 --> 02:35:32,539
What do I tell Mr. Pani?

2340
02:35:32,623 --> 02:35:33,789
Tell him she has eloped.

2341
02:35:35,123 --> 02:35:37,581
I carried her to school
with these hands, sir.

2342
02:35:37,914 --> 02:35:39,706
Using the same hands,
lead her to the wedding altar.

2343
02:35:43,039 --> 02:35:44,039
Careful, dear.

2344
02:35:44,498 --> 02:35:45,456
Your sari…

2345
02:35:47,623 --> 02:35:49,706
- If it weren't for you, Balu…
- Sir?

2346
02:35:50,414 --> 02:35:53,664
I would've driven her to Guntur in my Jeep
the very first day I saw her!

2347
02:35:54,331 --> 02:35:55,414
First day!

2348
02:35:56,998 --> 02:35:58,456
That's what you are doing right now, sir.
